title: snowy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and return pan to low heat, shaking to dry potatoes in large bowl.
Cream together the cheese and sour cream.
Add hot potatoes, one at a time.
Cream mixture and continue beating on high.
On low speed, add scallions, celery, green pepper, parsley, 1/4 cup butter, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until top is golden.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken tortilla bake
directions: Grease a 13x9 inch pan.
Break tortillas into fourths.
Boil chicken and debone.
Mix Velveeta and half of grated cheese with 1 cup broth and soups.
Heat until well blended.
Add chicken. Layer tortillas and cheese mixture.
End with cheese mixture on top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: laura's yogurt pie(good and easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and place in a pie shell.

title: orange cranberry nut bread
directions: Peel and separate orange from rind.
Add boiling water to juice and pulp from orange and shortening.
Put rind from orange through food chopper.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add rest of all ingredients.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Put butter into saucepan and add flour.
Add 1 cup of milk or stock, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
When starch granulars are cooked, remove from fire and add Worcestershire sauce, pepper and grated onion juice.
Separate eggs and add yolks to cream sauce.
Stir.
Flake salmon; add to sauce and egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites; fold the salmon mixture into the egg whites.
Turn into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Cook over low heat in saucepan until thick.

title: old-fashioned lemon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Serve warm.
May be refrigerated and reheated.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg and beat 1 minute. Mix flour, soda, salt, and spices; stir in raisins and pecans. Heat persimmon pulp to boiling; add all ingredients together, beating well. Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 inch pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. (In a loaf pan, bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.) Cake keeps well frozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts. Add flour mixture alternately with bananas and milk a little at a time.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and cook, breaking up with wooden spoon.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, sauce mix and vegetable juice.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain and layer vegetables. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine egg and water and then add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir first 1/2 hour.
Use 1 1/2 to 2 pounds pecan halves.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour mix into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend mushroom soup and milk.
Place rice into ungreased baking dish.
Stir in 1/2 of soup and milk mixture, mushrooms and 1/2 of dry onion soup mix.

title: corn casserole quartet
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High.

title: hot chicken salad pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shells, corn flakes and butter. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Precook the pie shells for 10 minutes at 400 degrees.
Fill pie shells with chicken mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and saute cornflakes.
Sprinkle this topping over two pies and bake 5 more minutes.
I cut the amount of onion in half and reduce the amount of corn flake crumbs.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and vanilla. Add baking soda and flour.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes and check. If not done, bake approximately 15 minutes more.

title: smothered okra beef dish
directions: Wash and cut okra.
Fry okra until no longer stringy.
Cook ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
When meat is done, combine it with okra and add tomatoes.
Cook on low fire about 1 hour or longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with dry onions.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Add pineapple juice, pear juice and peach juice to desired thickness.
Can add blueberries if you so desire.

title: cool and creamy cucumber ring
directions: Thinly slice 1 cucumber and arrange in bottom of lightly oiled 4-cup ring mold; set aside.
Peel, seed and coarsely chop remaining cucumbers.
With food processor or electric mixer, combine cream cheese, 1 cup chopped cucumber, sour cream, dill, lemon juice and soup mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining chopped cucumber.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Add the cooked, drained pasta and toss.
Then add 1 cup Italian dressing. Toss again thoroughly.
Serve chilled.

title: oyster stew
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients into smooth paste.
Stir into 1 pint oysters.
Simmer oyster mix over very low heat until edges begin to curl.
Add to 1 quart of heated milk and heat over very low heat (do not let boil).
Heavy cream added instead of part of the milk and some butter will add to the flavor.
This can heat for several hours; even better the second day.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside and crumble.
Slice onions thin.
Separate in rings and cook in bacon fat until tender. (Drain about half of the fat off first.)
Stir in sugar, vinegar, mustard, garlic powder and salt.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Combine with onion mixture and bacon.
Bake in a casserole or bean pot for 1 hour at 350°.
This makes a lot but it freezes well.

title: sue's special cake
directions: Grease and flour lightly a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on package.
Pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Cream butter.
Cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over the cake mixture.
Bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until tested done in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together just until mixed.
Add a small amount of milk, just enough to moisten.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: In greased baking dish, mix eggs, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add corn and enough milk to make soupy.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until thickened. Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash to 1/4-inch circles. Layer a 2-quart microwave bowl with yellow squash, dash of garlic salt and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. Toss on onion, tomato and peppers. Put a layer of zucchini and repeat previous seasonings. Make layers until all of the squash is in casserole. Cover and microwave 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apricot mold
directions: Blend Jell-O and water and refrigerate until partially set. Add apricots and pineapple (optional).
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: low-fat french toast
directions: You will also need Pam spray.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Cover with brown sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: aunt nells' tomato-cucumber soup
directions: Heat oil in a 2-quart pan over medium heat.
Add onion and carrot, cook and stir often, about 10 minutes.
Stir in basil, sugar and pepper.

title: artichoke spread *
directions: Drain artichokes thoroughly, pressing to remove excess liquid. In mixing bowl, mash artichokes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except vegetable dippers.
Cover and chill several hours. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Serve with assorted fresh raw vegetables.
Makes 1 1/3 cups dip.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.
Half recipe is plenty for family.

title: cheese, sausage and ground beef dish
directions: Mash sausage in frying pan.
Put lid on and simmer for 5 minutes or until done.
Pour off excess fat.
Add ground beef and stir until done.
Cut up cheese into mixture and stir until melted.
Do not cook any longer.
Serve on rice, potatoes or toast.

title: pumpkin upside cake
directions: Beat eggs; add next 6 ingredients.
Pour in ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle on 1 package dry yellow cake mix; melt 3/4 cup oleo and drizzle over cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dessert salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package.
Partially harden.
Mix in softened cream cheese and relish.
Refrigerate until firm. Sprinkle with crushed nuts for topping.

title: date and nut pudding
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup brown sugar in pan you bake pudding it.
In a bowl, cream together the next 6 ingredients.
Add the dates and pecans.
Pour this batter on top of the sugar water (do not stir).
Bake in slow oven, about 325°, for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir all together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do not grease or flour pan.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: stone jar nut cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco, then add the eggs, spices, and salt.
Gradually add the flour and soda, then add the milk and nuts.
Let stand one hour.
Fill your cookie sheet and bake the cookies at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes only.
The cookies will appear not to be cooked done.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cut and wash chicken and boil.
Add chopped celery, green onions, onion bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning when chicken is almost done.
Boil until vegetables are tender. Remove skin and debone and chop chicken.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter baking sheets.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, stir in egg and vanilla, then add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by 1/4 cup of dough onto sheets, leaving 3 inches between cookies. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until browned.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-large saucepan and cook on high for 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce to simmer and cook until rice is done, usually 20 to 30 minutes.
With this rice, stirring in between cooking will keep vegetables distributed.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix, freeze and serve.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Combine molasses, shortening, butter and water in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients to liquid and blend well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chile verde with pork
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces and dredge in flour and salt. Brown in hot oil.
Add onions, chiles and garlic.
Cook until softened.
Stir in remaining flour.
Add tomatoes and water. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is tender.

title: lemon chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1/2 hour to let flavors blend.
Serve as sandwiches or in the bowl with crackers.
Very low in fat when you follow directions!

title: cracker jack
directions: Put popped corn in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly around the edge.
Cook 5 minutes more. Remove from heat; stir in soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn and stir until well coated.
Bake 1 hour in 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Add the first 3 ingredients and then cook on medium heat until it reaches 310° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add cinnanom oil and then food coloring.
Butter cookie sheet and pour the ingredients in the cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break with a spoon.
Shake in powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch drops cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until smooth and creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift all dry ingredients. Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture, beating constantly, on low speed.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: bailey bones(dog biscuits)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out treats with cookie cutter (bone shape).
Microwave at 50% for 5 to 10 minutes, turning every 2 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until dry. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Rinse beans; combine with water in large pot.
Heat to boiling; cook 2 minutes.
Turn off heat; cover.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and carrots in oil for 10 minutes.
Add to beans and liquid, ham bone and thyme.
Heat to boiling; cover.
Simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove bone and dice meat.
Spoon about 2 cups beans and 1/2 liquid in processor or blender.
Stir back into pot along with the ham.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Heat slowly until hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and let cool. Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Fold eggs in cooked, mashed squash. Add milk.
Put layers of Ritz cracker crumbs, squash and cheese. On top, sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs. Dot with oleo and cook for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Add 1/4 cup sugar to whipping cream.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cheese sauce(for cabbage stuffed with ham and cheese)
directions: Melt in saucepan butter; stir in flour until blended.
Stir in milk, slowly.
When the sauce is smooth and hot, reduce the heat and stir in cheese.
Season the sauce with salt, paprika, cayenne and mustard.
Stir the sauce until the cheese is melted.

title: chicken and potato bake
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking dish.
Arrange in layers the potatoes, chicken and onion slices.
Blend soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries, reserving liquids in a medium saucepan. Sprinkle gelatin over liquid mixture and let stand 1 minute. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until gelatin dissolves; remove from heat. Add cream cheese, stirring until smooth. Stir in fruit, cola beverage and pecans. Pour into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold. Cover and refrigerate.

title: coffee spice bars
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and egg; add coffee.
Mix together dry ingredients and stir into above.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread in jelly roll pan 10 x 15-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, spread as a topping:
2 cups powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 tablespoons soft margarine and hot coffee to make a soft frosting.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: sensational salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.
Makes two quarts.

title: simon and garfunkel chicken
directions: Pound chicken flat; salt and pepper lightly.
Lay 2 slices of Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Dot with butter; roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Dip each piece in egg, then bread crumbs and place in a baking dish.
Melt butter and add spices. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Pour wine over chicken and bake another 20 minutes.

title: cap'n crunch candy
directions: Mix cereals, peanuts and pretzels together.
Melt chips; pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop in mounds on wax paper. Let cool.
Makes a lot.
Store in covered container.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Whip the cream until soft peaks.
Bring lemons, egg yolks and milk to a boil and cool.
Add this and the whipped cream to the fruit.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: sweet and sour apples
directions: Core and slice apples; set aside.
Combine cornstarch and ginger in skillet; gradually stir in apple juice, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Stir in apples and simmer, covered, 5 to 10 minutes, or until apples are crisp-tender.
Serves 4 with 81 calories per serving.
Great with broiled chicken!

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Let cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve with fresh fruit. Yields about 2 cups.

title: chocolate skillet cake
directions: Mix cocoa with cold water.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Add cocoa mixture and half the flour and blend.
Add milk and blend.
Add remaining flour and vanilla and blend.

title: banana blitz
directions: Pour water in blender; add jello and blend at low until dissolved.
Add ice cubes and stir until partially melted; blend 30 seconds.
Mixture should be cold.
Add milk and banana slices; blend until smooth.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill until set.

title: sugar cream pie #3
directions: Melt butter and add sugar and cornstarch.
Stir until smooth. Add milk and cook over medium heat until thick like pudding.
Stir in vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg or cinnamon and place in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix the cake mix, butter and water until blended.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Add the last 4 ingredients to the Jell-O.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of rectangular cake pan. Follow with a layer of crushed pineapple, then dry cake mix, melted butter, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain and keep warm.
In the meantime, prepare white sauce, adding onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shredded cheese all at once.
Turn 1/2 of macaroni into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 cheese sauce over it.
Repeat, forming layers.
Sprinkle the buttered crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it.
Now, go ahead, select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. and check that rum again for quality.
It must be just right.
Try it again.
With an electric beater, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and beat again. Meanwhile, make certain that rum is of best quality.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust!)
directions: Blend
margarine,
sugar and flour.
Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch well buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: baked curried salmon salad
directions: Drain, bone and coarsely flake salmon.
Mix all ingredients except crumbs, lemon slices and paprika.
Spoon into 6 greased ramekins.
Sprinkle with crumbs; top each with lemon slice and dust with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: winnie's chili beans
directions: Brown together the ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese and olive biscuits
directions: Blot dry stuffed olives.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add oil, milk, nutmeg, paprika, Parmesan cheese and grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix well and knead a little. Shape balls with your hands a little smaller than ping-pong balls. Work these balls around an olive. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. The olive should be in the center.

title: grama's noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make firm ball.
Roll out and cut into long strips.
Let dry, then cook.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor.
Set aside.
Mix pudding as directed.
(Use less milk, 1/4 or 1/2 cup less, to make firmer).
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; add Cool Whip to this.
Then add this mixture to pudding.
Alternate cookie mix with pudding mix in container (can use clean kid's pail).
Can also add gummy worms, etc., to top.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with onions in small amount of shortening. Add tomatoes, chili powder and salt and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes; add cooled spaghetti.
Continue to simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix preserves, jelly, horseradish and mustard and pour over block of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage flavored thyme turkey burgers
directions: Combine turkey, bread crumbs, onion, egg, yogurt, fennel seed, thyme and seasonings.
Shape into 6 patties.
Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Cook patties over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 turkey burgers, 100 calories each, 10 calories less per burger with egg substitute.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put all of the ingredients in baking dish and stir.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy round steak casserole
directions: Pound or have butcher pound large slice round steak.
Trim fat and cut in serving slices.
Brown meat in light oil.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pans.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir to blend.

title: ten minute chili
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Drain off fat and add garlic salt, onion salt and chili powder.
Next, add tomatoes, beans and water if needed.
Simmer a few minutes or a few hours, depending on how much time you have.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil in heavy pan. Fry onion and garlic until soft.
Add beef.
Cook and stir until crumbly.
Mix in salt, pepper, rosemary and tomato paste.
Blend with water.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup (37-40 calories per cup)
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 15 minutes. Add next six ingredients and cook. Finally add tomato soup.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until tender; set aside.
Cook noodles.

While noodles cook, on low heat, saute bell pepper and onion in margarine until tender; add Worcestershire sauce, a can of cream of chicken (may want to cook in microwave first), then add Velveeta and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook long enough for cheese to melt.
Drain noodles and take chicken off bones.
Add all ingredients.

title: lunch room peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well and roll in round rolls. Chill and slice.

title: buffet strawberry pineapple mold(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in partly thawed strawberries, pineapple and salt.
Pour half gelatin into an 8-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Keep remaining gelatin at room temperature.
Beat cream cheese until softened.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth.
Carefully spread in even layer over firm gelatin in mold.
Refrigerate.
Chill remaining gelatin until partly thickened and spoon over cheese layer.
Chill mold at least 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold on platter and garnish with greens and pineapple rings, if you wish.

title: oatmeal raisin jumbos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat in oil and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in flour, baking powder and allspice.
Stir in oats and raisins.

title: beef cheese casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Melt cheese and stir in Ro-Tel. Mix with cooked noodles.
Add extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot through.
Serve with salad and bread sticks.

title: maryland crab meat au gratin
directions: Mix together crab meat, white sauce, lemon juice and onion. Put into buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs, paprika and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Flavor is improved if prepared 12 hours ahead and kept in refrigerator before baking in oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: clyde's coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sour cream, eggs and instant pudding. Batter will be thick.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 of cinnamon sugar mixture over batter, then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cook onions a little before adding to other ingredients.
Remove seeds from chilies.
Beat eggs; add corn and other ingredients.
Grate cheese and put on top.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: disappearing brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease sides and bottom of 9-inch square pan with butter or margarine.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done, crumble and drain.
Mix with cheese and sprinkle in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Pour carefully into pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marvelous microwave marmalade
directions: Quarter oranges and
shred
in a food processor.
Place the shredded orange and an
equal amount of sugar in a 1-quart glass bowl.
Mix well
and
place in microwave.
Set at Medium range and cook until	slightly
thick,
about
6 to 8 minutes. Cover and refrigerate.

title: no bake quick chocolate cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, cocoa and milk slowly until sugar is melted.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until melted and add oats.
Mix well.
Drop while hot by teaspoonful on wax paper. Cool.

title: frost on the pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin. Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until creamy.
Use as dip for strawberries, cherries, oranges, apples, etc.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter and cheese together.
Blend crabmeat into butter and cheese.
Serve over fondue.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili sauce and grape jelly and make into 1-inch balls.
Brown in 1/4 cup shortening.
Pour off grease.
Combine in skillet the chili sauce and grape jelly.
Melt and dissolve.
Add balls.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pizza bagels
directions: On each half of bagel spread butter.
Put 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on each half (open faced).
Add Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, pizza sauce, mushrooms and other toppings.
Bake approximately 7 minutes on 300° or until cheese is melted.

title: orange roughy
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in lemon juice, parsley, chives, dill and cayenne pepper.
Lay fish in single layer in 9-inch square pan. Pour batter mixture over fish.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Take out and keep warm.
Boil juices over high heat until about 1/4 cup is left.
Pour over fish.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in dry cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Mix wafer crumbs and butter.
Place in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator.
Set strawberry, lime and orange jello with 1 1/2 cups water in separate dishes.
Dissolve lemon jello with 1/2 cup hot water and pineapple juice.
Set until partially thick, then fold in whipped cream.
Cut the other 3 jellos in cubes and add. Spread over crust and set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Also add sugar to the lemon jello.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Heat to a boiling point.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and dissolve.
Add oats.
Drop mixture quickly on wax paper by the tablespoons or pour mixture into a buttered 9 x 2-inch pan and cool.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Over medium heat, saute onion and curry powder, stirring
constantly 3 to 5 minutes.
Let mixture cool.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in hot 400° oven 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer until middle of pie is firm.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Combine onion, spices and relish with meat; set aside.
Make white sauce by melting butter in a skillet, stirring in flour, then milk.
Bring to a boil or heat until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Grease a casserole dish and prepare 2 layers like this: three tortillas in pieces, 1/2 the sour cream sauce, 1/2 the meat mixture and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Repeat these layers.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 20 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions on box. Bake in two greased and floured round pans. Split layers with thread when cool, making 4 layers.

title: grandma elliott's sauerkraut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape to form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes; serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix thoroughly
and put in refrigerator until moldable. Roll in pecans.

title: korean pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate over pork chops 1 to 2 hours. Grill or broil.

title: italian sausage and zucchini
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown sausage.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Remove accumulated fat.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, lemon juice, salt and oregano.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese and lots of crusty bread.
Serves 6.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Fry chicken until almost done.
Get it good and brown.
Place chicken in heavy pan with a lid.
Pour mushroom soup over chicken and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in oven and let it cook until soup has thickened.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick.
Cool until lukewarm. Combine eggs and yeast in warm water with sugar.
Mix well and add to other mixture.
Then add flour to make a soft dough.
Knead and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise one hour.
Punch down and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter and fold over as Parker House rolls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 rolls.

title: homemade beef stew
directions: Cut beef in 1-inch cubes; roll in flour and fry in hot oils. Follow directions on beef stew packet.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Then add vegetables and cook until done.
Season to taste, if more is needed.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread butter on each slice. Place slices on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan. Brown sausage; drain and sprinkle over bread.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Mix egg, milk (or half and half) and salt.
Pour this mixture over the cheese and sausage.
Cover and chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Put breasts in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cajun chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In oven roasting pan, melt margarine in oven. Remove. Stir in remaining seasonings.
Gradually add cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add onions.
Mix well. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: upside-down sausage cornbread
directions: Crumble sausage into small pieces and brown.
Drain off fat and spread about 3/4 of it on the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions (i.e., mix with egg and milk) and pour over sausage, spreading evenly in the pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes (until done).
While cornbread is baking, add the soup (undiluted) to the pan with the remaining sausage.

Stir over low heat until bottom of pan is clear of sausage; add cheese (shredded, cubed or otherwise broken into pieces) and stir until cheese is melted and cheese and sausage are uniformly distributed through the sauce.
When cornbread is done, invert pan over large plate to remove it; cut into squares and serve with sauce.

title: aunt artie bell's chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken, onion and eggs.
Mix soups and pour over.

title: pork roast
directions: Rinse pork roast under water.
Pat Nature's Seasons all over roast. Flour roast	very
well.
Brown on top of range in butter flavored Crisco,
well on all sides. When browned well, pour off fat and add
2 to 3 cans of Coke depending on size of roast. Cover and
cook
very
slow
until roast is tender and done.

title: holiday strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Stir carefully. Turn batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn onto cooling rack.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo, mix well and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rosti potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and shred.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Add potatoes and salt; cook until heated and yellow. Stir in bacon, onion and cheese.
Press potatoes into a round flat cake pan and sprinkle with water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until crust forms on bottom.
Shake pan once or twice to prevent burning.
Place serving plate over potatoes and invert so crust side is up.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: low-fat pasta soup
directions: In a large pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add broth and 3 cups water; next add mango, garlic, celery, carrot and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and cook about 15 minutes, then add pasta and squash.
Cook for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a small boiler with enough water to cover. Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and butter and stir until melted.
Pour peach mixture into a deep baking dish.
Take pastry dough, roll thin and cut into 1-inch strips.
Add strips to the peach mixture, being sure to cover them entirely in the mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place the leftover pastry strips in crisscross fashion on the top of the dish.
Bake in oven until cobbler bubbles and crust is brown.
Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to package directions.
Crumble and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer onion, pepper, tomatoes, ham and eggs.
Mix together relish, juice and mayonnaise.
Pour over layer and mix lightly.
Top with bacon bits.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours.

title: canned kraut
directions: You will need 12 quart jars.

title: baked flounder
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until half done.
Add white sauce and shrimp; set aside.
Put heavy foil in baking pan. Lay flounder on foil; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread white sauce mixture over fish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Combine margarine and both sugars; mix well.
Stir in milk, orange juice and egg.
Mix in all the remaining ingredients.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; bring to rolling boil.
Turn heat to low; add red jello.
Cook 8 minutes.
Stir often.
Cool.
Pour into a clean jar and store in refrigerator.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Squeeze dry and chop spinach.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add picante sauce, onion, tomato sauce, salt and oregano; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and mix in noodles.
Place 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9 baking dish.
Cover with spinach.
Top with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with corn.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cover with cheese and bake until cheese is melted. Garnish with sour cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake in jelly roll pan that has been greased and floured.
Use only 3/4 of batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven when melted.
In large bowl, beat eggs, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add cheese, then add spinach, thawed and drained.
Pour in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and let cool for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite-size squares.

title: crappie on the grill
directions: On a large sheet of aluminum foil brushed with 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine, lay several fillets and top with remaining ingredients.
Seal foil tightly.
Cook on grill until aluminum expands, approximately 20 minutes.
This recipe works well with most fish, but crappie, bluegill and walleye are best.

title: herbed fish fillets
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cornmeal and seasonings.
Dip fish in egg and milk mixed and coat with cornmeal.
Place on cookie sheet (15 x 10-inch).
Drizzle butter over fish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes (or until golden brown).
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches; set aside.
Melt butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except brown sugar and walnuts, in mixing bowl until a smooth batter is formed.
Pour batter into baking dish over melted butter and spread drained sliced peaches over the top of the batter.
Combine brown sugar and walnuts and sprinkle over peaches.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 1 hour or until browned and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: new potatoes
directions: Peel new potatoes and cook in water until done.
Drain liquid. Roll them in corn meal.
Put them in a greased frying pan and cook until golden brown.

title: zucchini and italian sausage soup(serves 10)
directions: In a large Dutch oven (pan), cook sausage over medium heat until lightly browned.
Drain fat and discard.
Put sausage aside. Add garlic and onions to Dutch oven, stirring until limp.
Stir in tomatoes (including liquid) and cut into small pieces.
Add sausage, broth and herbs.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add parsley, green pepper, zucchini and noodles and simmer 25 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes(potatoes for 50)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into roaster. Melt butter and add flour. Mix and add milk slowly, stirring constantly. Cook until thick. Add salt. Pour liquid over potatoes. Bake at 325° until done. About an hour.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients; gradually fold into egg mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Put onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll and let cool.
Unroll carefully and spread with cream cheese filling.
Roll up, chill and serve.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Mash up graham crackers with oleo, then cover with coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour 1 can Eagle milk and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in a 9-inch or 13-inch pan.

title: garbage bread
directions: Will also need a basting brush.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread cheese on meat and make a roll. Cut rolls and place on crackers or rye bread.

title: maple baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With a sharp knife, cut each squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out all the seeds and any stringy filaments.
Bake until tender.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries or fruit pie mix.

title: tiffany's cream cheese sugar cake
directions: Spread 1 can of crescent rolls in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla flavoring. Spread over crescent rolls.
Spread another can of crescent rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Pour one stick of melted margarine over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with lots of brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: polynesian pork]
directions: Cook pork in margarine until brown; drain.
Drain juice from pineapple and reserve.
Combine juice with Russian dressing, soy sauce, vinegar and salt.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to juice mix.
Pour over meat.
Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 6 generously.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12 inch pizza pan, with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle parmesan over all.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields: 6-8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well; makes a big batch.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and flour tube pan.
Bake at 250° 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: raisin-date cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, orange and lemon peel, spices and baking soda.
Add flour and blend.
Stir in raisins and dates.
Drop heaping tablespoonful 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Spread lightly with back of floured spoon.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: old fashion oatmeal bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in oats, brown sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve. In large bowl, mix 2 cups flour with milk mixture and yeast.
Add enough flour to form soft dough.
Knead on floured board 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise again (1/2 hour).
Pour out on board; knead gently.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise (1/2 hour).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Saute pepper.
Add soup and spices and simmer 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Grease or spray with cooking spray a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place noodles on bottom of pan.
Pour meat sauce over noodles. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Arrange mushrooms over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove foil last 10 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes, then cut into squares.
May sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Works well in microwave.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix onion and sour cream together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange sauerkraut on top, then layer of crumbled corned beef, then layer of grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs; drizzle with butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: homemade pork sausage
directions: Mix fat and lean pork.	Start out by adding the seasonings listed above.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook a small patty and taste. Adjust seasonings to taste.

title: tarragon butter
directions: Chop tarragon finely.
Soften butter.
Chop dill.
Make a powder of crushed bay leaves.
Beat softened butter until creamy. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place butter on waxed paper and form into a roll or other shape with a flat bladed knife.
A pastry bag can be used to make more intricate shapes.
Allow butter to "rest" in refrigerator at least 2 hours so butter will completely absorb flavor of herbs.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together with just enough evaporated milk to make dough hold together.
It must be pliable. Roll quite thin.
Cut in strips.
Let dry a few hours, then drop in a broth.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Add celery, walnuts, raisins and mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill and serve on lettuce. Makes 6 servings.

title: paste for children's play
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cold water in top of double boiler. Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Add alum and oil of cloves to preserve.
Seal into jars.
Paste will set to stiffer consistency.
Lasts indefinitely if kept sealed.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and sterilize jars.
Put onions in bottom of jars.
Fill each jar with cucumbers (pack tightly).
Combine sugar, cider vinegar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed for syrup (mix cold; do not heat).
Stir syrup well and pour into jars, covering cucumbers.
Put lids on jars.
It is not necessary to seal.
Refrigerate for at least 5 days before using.
Pickles will remain good for at least 9 months in the refrigerator.

title: barbara's mexican meat dish
directions: Butter bottom of long, deep pan.
While hamburger meat is browning with onion and bell pepper, mix in bowl Ro-Tel, enchilada sauce, canned vegetables and can of cream of mushroom soup.
After buttering pan, pour a layer of chips on bottom.
After draining meat, mix with other ingredients; stir.

title: marble brownies
directions: In small saucepan, combine water, margarine and chocolate. Melt together.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour and sugar.
Then add chocolate mixture, sour cream, eggs and soda. Blend all with electric mixer until blended and set aside.
In deep mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar and then add 1 egg. Blend all 3 together well with mixer.
Pour chocolate mixture into long flat pan.
Drop cream cheese mixture by small spoons over chocolate batter.
Then swirl with knife to make marble effect. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Layer tortilla shells, chili, cheese and sour cream in a large baking dish, layering until all ingredients are used, ending with chili on top.
Place in a preheated 475° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Empty apples and juice into Pyrex dish.
Cream butter, sugar, flour and cheese.
Place over apples and pour half and half over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Recipe doubles easily.
You can freeze and bake later.

title: cheezy broccoli
directions: Place unopened package of broccoli in microwave.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, turning over after 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip, pudding and milk.
Crush Oreos into very fine pieces.
Make layers, alternating between Oreos first, then mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with Oreos on top.
Place in the freezer in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 or 10-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: a better chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12-cup Bundt pan with cooking spray and dust lightly with granulated sugar.
Combine raisins, chocolate chips and nuts with cornstarch in a small bowl; stir to coat and set aside.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding and cool to room temperature.
Add pudding, eggs and chocolate chips to cake mix.
Bake in a greased tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing (any kind).

title: 7-up jello
directions: Heat applesauce and stir in dry jello.
Remove from heat and stir in 7-Up.
Let sit a few minutes to let foam disappear.
Pour into mold.
May double or triple recipe.
This is a very firm jello and slices well.

title: sausage balls
directions: In food processor, mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick until well blended.
Form small balls out of mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° to 400° for about 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream together tuna and cream cheese.
Add onion and pickles. Form into a ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix salt and pepper with flour.
Mix cheese and margarine. Add flour to cheese and margarine.
Add rice krispies.
Roll into balls smaller than a quarter, flatten.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bottoms are light brown.
Freezes well.

title: grandma allen's fudge sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan the first 4 ingredients.
Add boiling water and butter.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Add vanilla. Sauce can be refrigerated and kept if you can!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, brown hamburger and diced onion; drain off fat.
Add the tomato soup with two cans water.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, two to three hours, until desired thickness.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Stir-fry ground
beef
in oil until it loses red color. Add garlic,
salt,
pepper,
onion,
green
pepper
and
chili powder. Cook 5 minutes or until onion is wilted.
Add all but olives and cheese and turn into a 2 quart or larger casserole. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese and olives and bake
more	minutes
or until cheese is melted. Serves 8.

title: barbecue beef on a bun
directions: Dry roast on paper towels.
In a deep, heavy pot, heat oil and add roast.
Brown on all sides.
Add all the other ingredients. Cover and simmer slowly over medium to low heat for 3 to 4 hours until beef can be easily shredded.
With two forks, shred the beef and mix into the sauce.
Taste and add salt, if necessary. Serve on hot buttered buns.

title: honey dressing
directions: Combine
dry ingredients; stir in honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.	Slowly pour salad oil into mixture, beating constantly with rotary or electric beater.
Yields 2 cups.

title: fancy baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash and core apples, taking care not to pierce the bottoms.
Prick skins every inch or so with the tip of a sharp knife.
Mix cookies and almonds with butter and pack into apples.
Place apples in baking dish and sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar over each.
Add wine and water to the pan. Place pan on upper shelf of oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Transfer apples to serving or storage dish.
Pour pan juices into saucepan. Simmer over high heat until juices have become syrupy.
Pour over apples.
Apples will keep in the refrigerator for 3 days.

title: scallops with mushrooms
directions: Combine the butter, wine, parsley, scallions and sherry in the crockery pot.
Bring to a boil on the high setting (300°), stirring constantly.
Add the scallops and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on the high setting for 15 minutes or until the scallops are tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.
Don't overcook the scallops.

title: gourmet chili
directions: Heat oil in a 4 or 5-quart pot. Saute onion until clear; add peppers and garlic and saute until limp.
Add chili powder, cumin, oregano, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly, stirring often, until meat is brown and broken apart.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans, including liquid.
Stir well to combine ingredients.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Mix all together and spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
until lightly browned.

title: honey-baked drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine the flour and pepper in a plastic bag.
Place the drumsticks in the bag with the flour.
Shake to coat.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Roll the floured drumsticks in the margarine to coat them. Bake for 20 minutes.
Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons margarine in a small saucepan.
Stir in the honey, lemon juice and soy sauce until well mixed.
Turn the drumsticks over in the pan and pour the honey sauce over all.
Bake for 30 minutes, basting once with the sauce in the pan until drumsticks are tender and well glazed.

title: sour salad dressing
directions: Blend on high speed for 10 seconds.
Makes 2/3 cup; will keep long time.

title: hopping john
directions: Saute onions in butter; add remaining ingredients except for rice.
Heat all together.
Add rice; fluff together.
Add jalapeno peppers to taste for even better dish.

title: tater puffs
directions: Combine and work all ingredients together.
Form into size of ball desired.
Bake or fry until brown.

title: healthy veggie-beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, breaking finely into pieces. Drain in colander and return to skillet. Add seasonings and taco sauce.
Stir in all the cream of celery soup (undiluted, no water). Add both packages of vegetables, partially thawed. Toss and mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan, well sprayed with Pam. Bake 40 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with the shredded cheese. Bake another 10 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread(refrigerator rise)
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl and add water.
Blend and mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup whole wheat flour and mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add white flour and stir until soft dough is formed.
On floured surface, knead for 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Cover with plastic wrap and a towel. Let rest for 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half and form into 2 loaves.
Place in bread pans sprayed with vegetable oil spray. Spray tops of loaves with vegetable oil spray and cover with a plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cover with paper or cloth towel until cool.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins until tender, then drain. Cream sugar and butter, add egg yolks. Mix well, add vanilla. Add flour, then raisins. Last of all add well beaten egg whites.

title: schaum torte
directions: Whip egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar slowly and then vanilla.
Beat on high speed for 25 minutes. Spread in greased 10-inch form.
Set in cold oven.
Bake at 225° for about 75 minutes, until top is dry to touch and slightly brown.
Shut off oven and open door just a crack (a paper width) until cool, usually overnight.
Transfer to torte plate; cover with whipped cream and your choice of fruit.
Serve.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Whisk together milk and French vanilla pudding in large bowl. Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly by hand.
Layer the bottom of truffle dish with graham crackers and follow with a layer of pudding mixture (approximately 1/3).
Continue alternating a layer of graham crackers and pudding mixture, ending with a layer of graham crackers.
Microwave can of frosting for approximately 30 seconds.
Spread on top of layer of graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 8 hours and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake at 400 degrees until an inserted knife comes out clean.
For different taste add 1 tablespoon chopped onion and 2 tablespoons chopped green pepper to the corn mixture.

title: zesty slow cooker italian roast
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and celery in 3 1/2-qt. slow cooker. Season roast with pepper and place on top. Mix soup and water. Pour over all. Cover and cook on Low 10 to 12 hours. For thicker gravy, mix 1/4 c. all-purpose flour with 1/2 C. water. Remove beef and keep warm. Add flour mixture to slow cooker. Turn heat to High. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, about 10 minutes.

title: sinfully sweet potatoes
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into a greased 2 quart casserole.
Cover with topping and bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add blended eggs and oil.
Add remaining 5 ingredients.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in with cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, pecans and orange peel.
Refrigerate.

title: summer jello cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, dissolve jello in 3/4 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and let cool.
After cake has cooled (20 to 30 minutes) poke holes in cake with fork while still in pan, about one inch apart.
Pour jello into holes.
Frost.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Cook hot dogs.
Cut into little bite size pieces.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Grease four 8-inch cake pans and dust with flour.
Separate eggs.
Set whites aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter well. Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well, then add peanut butter and vanilla, blending well.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add beans and rest of the ingredients. Bake in casserole in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Blend ingredients, except potatoes, in a shallow pan.
Add potatoes and turn to coat.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour or until tender and golden brown.
Turn occasionally.

title: turkey 'n' stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/3 cup butter.
Stir in stuffing mix and set aside.
Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Stir in soup, sour cream and water.
Stir in turkey and 1/2 stuffing mix.
Transfer into shallow baking dish. Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes, covered.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss together with other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix butter or margarine and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar; mix well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.

title: dreamsicle pudding
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 3 ice cubes to a cup and fill with cold water.
Add to dissolved Jell-O.
Mix well, set aside to cool for 5 minutes.
With electric mixer, add dry pudding to Jell-O.
Mix about 1 minute.
Let stand 15 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: georgia's cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft (with salt); drain water, all but 2 tablespoons.
Mix cornstarch and milk in a separate cup.
Pour mixture into potatoes.
Add butter and cheese; cook on stove until cheese is melted and thickened.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs with milk in bowl.
Add sifted salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a thin batter.
Heat 1/2 to 1-inch oil in saucepan.
Pour batter into funnel, closing openings with finger.
Drizzle in spiral into hot oil.
Fry until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: five layer taco dip
directions: Combine dressing and beans.
Mix well.
In 9-inch pie plate layer vegetables and dressing, saving some of the cheese and olives for topping.
Chill and serve with corn chips, tortilla chips, crackers or raw vegetables such as celery, carrots, broccoli or cauliflower.

title: hasty butterscotch frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in milk; cook until mixture comes to a boil. Gradually add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat until of spreading consistency. Thin with milk, if necessary.

title: steeplechase eggs
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Butter one side of bread with softened butter and set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add mushrooms and onions and saute over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain and set aside.
Cook the sausage; drain and break into bite size pieces. In a buttered 7 x 11-inch shallow pan, layer half the bread with the buttered side down, mushrooms and onions, sausage, then cheese.
Repeat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients but jello.
Pour jello over mixture and stir.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together.
Place in greased and floured bread tins. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.
It freezes well!

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: red cinnamon apple rings
directions: Make syrup of water, sugar, cinnamon candies and food coloring.
Pare and core apples; slice into 1/2-inch rings.
Cook apple rings in syrup until tender.
Use as garnish for pork and poultry.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend and chill.
Split cake layers.
Spread all but one cup of mixture between layers. Combine remaining cup with Cool Whip and frost the cake.
Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Combine can of crushed pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add lemon jello and cream cheese to mixture; let cool. Fold in apples, celery, nuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate in mold and serve chilled.

title: cold cucumber soup 2
directions: Trim scallions, retaining most of the green ends and chop. Peel potatoes and cucumber and cut into cubes.
Heat oil and add all ingredients.
With lid on, cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add hot chicken stock; bring to boil, then simmer slowly with lid off until vegetables are tender.
Liquidize in blender; adjust seasoning, strain, cool and refrigerate overnight.
Serve in chilled bowls with chopped fresh chives.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: joe's italian spaghetti
directions: Fry onions, garlic and pepper in olive oil until onions are lightly browned.
Add meat, brown slightly and cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: couche-couche
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch iron pot.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add water and milk.
Mixture should be thick but not too dry.
Put into hot oil. Cover to steam and form a crust, about 10 minutes. Uncover. Stir to break into small pieces. Stir frequently, about 15 minutes. Serve with cold milk as a cereal.

title: salmon patties
directions: Crumble crackers in salmon.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Make small patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: crunchy chicken crepes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Stir in green pepper, chicken broth, wine, celery and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Remove 2 tablespoons of liquid and dissolve cornstarch in liquid.
Return to pan and stir into chicken mixture. Bring to a boil and add walnuts.
Fill crepes; lay in a row, using a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Mornay Sauce.
Bake and serve.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large bowl. Mix eggs, buttermilk and oil. Add to dry ingredients and mix well. Store in a covered container in the refrigerator and use anytime in the next 6 weeks.

title: the brigittine monk's fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and cook exactly 6 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients. Beat until firm.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking pan. Cool to room temperature, then store overnight in the refrigerator.
Makes 5 very fattening pounds.

title: gooey caramel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, combine pecans, sugar, margarine, corn syrup and cinnamon. Mix well. On floured surface, place biscuits side by side, pinching together at edges to make a solid sheet of dough. Brush mixture over sheet of dough. Roll dough into a log and cut into 12 rolls, lining them inside deep dish baker. Repeat with remaining biscutis. Pour remainder of mixture evenly over rolls and bake for 25 minutes.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: anadama bread
directions: In a large bowl, slowly pour boiling water over cornmeal, stirring continually to avoid lumps.
Let cool 1 hour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add to cornmeal along with other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, cover and let rise until doubled. Turn out onto a floured board.
Knead 5 minutes, then divide and shape into 2 loaves.
Place in buttered 7 x 4-inch loaf pans and let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch strips; combine milk and egg.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture.
Mix flour, garlic salt, onion salt, pepper, paprika and potato flakes.
Dip chicken in flour mixture. Heat oil (test oil with drop of water; if it pops, it's ready). Put in chicken pieces; fry for 5 minutes on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with mashed potatoes and gravy or sauces.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices; layer on pizza pan as directed on package.
Bake and set aside to cool.

title: baked pork and beans
directions: When you are cooking cabbage, set in nearby place in a small dish (on top of range), a small amount of vinegar; it will absorb the cabbage odor while cooking.
It works wonderfully.

title: 0atmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except oats, flour, and raisins or nuts.

title: gingered cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, discarding tough outer leaves.
Add carrots and onion with cabbage.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then toss with cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate and serve cold.
Serves 4.

title: dan's cowboy stew
directions: Place butter in cast-iron skillet or pot.
Melt butter. Slowly drop meat in hot butter and stir until meat turns grey or is medium done.
As meat begins to brown, add onion (thinly sliced) and the potatoes, chopped fine.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook at medium heat until potatoes are soft.
Add chili powder to your taste.
Feeds 4.

title: prawns - spiced and brewed
directions: Pour all ingredients into a slow cooker and cook covered for 5 hours.
Cut prawns along their back from end to just before the tail, leaving the shell and tail on.
Remove the vein; rinse and refrigerate until ready to use.
After 5 hours of cooking ingredients, turn slow cooker to high and add enough water to fill the slow cooker to above half full.
Cook an additional 1/2 hour. Add prawns and cook until they turn pink, about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove shells and eat hot or cold.
Enjoy!

title: apple crisp
directions: Layer the sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cinnamon in the boiling water and pour over apple slices.
In separate bowl, combine cake mix, butter and brown sugar.
Mix well; it will be crumbly.
Sprinkle this over the apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.
M-m good!

title: one dish chicken & stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, 1 1/4 cup boiling water and 4 tablespoons margarine.
Spoon stuffing across center of shallow baking dish. Place chicken on each side of stuffing.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Mix soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 400° for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
In a large mixing bowl mix all ingredients together.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Place them on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Note that the uncooked sausage meat balls can be frozen.

title: sue's cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Mix together nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Grease a Bundt pan and layer 1/3 of nut mixture on bottom, then 1/2 cake mixture, then 1/3 nut mixture and rest of cake batter.
Top with remaining 1/3 nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Bon Appitite!

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef
in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil and add green pepper, onions and garlic.	Drain excess fat and add all other ingredients.
Mix
well and bake in large greased casserole at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage.
Make layers of cabbage, onion rings, bell pepper rings and pimentos.
Over the whole thing, sprinkle 1 cup sugar.
Do not stir.
Heat together vinegar, salad oil, salt, celery seed and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over cabbage mixture; refrigerate for 12 hours, if possible.
This seems to improve with several hours refrigeration.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, combine ground beef, water, tomato juice, tomato paste, minced onion, chili powder, salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes; stir often.
Add uncooked spaghetti and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese. Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: brownie peanut butter cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine brownie mix, water, oil, and egg.
Beat 50 strokes with a spoon.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Press 1 mini peanut butter cup in center until top edge of candy is even with the batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brownie is set.
Do not overbake!
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: stuffed tomato cups
directions: Cut tops
off
tomatoes; scoop out pulp.
Chop tops and pulp; drain.
Cut
sawtooth
edges
around
shells;
drain. Sprinkle inside
with
salt
and basil.
In skillet brown beef with onion; drain.
Stir in pulp, croutons, 1/2 teaspoon salt and Worcestershire;
stuff
shells.
Sprinkle
tomatoes
with cheese. Place in shallow baking dish; fill dish with 1/2 inch water.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Trim with parsley, if desired. Serves 4.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and milk. Roll out into a dough. Put apples on dough and sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour onto rolled out dough. Roll up like a jelly roll. Cut in slices. Melt butter in pan. Put slices in melted butter or margarine. In a saucepan, bring to a boil the water and sugar. Pour over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Delicious!

title: decorator icing
directions: Beat Crisco 5 minutes.
Put in egg whites and beat 3 minutes. Put in vanilla and mix.
Then put in sugar and mix by hand.

title: cookie delight
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Gently stir in whipped topping and half the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into bottoms of 8-ounce plastic cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
If desired, decorate with gummy worms.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Pour scalded milk over butter and sugar, stirring to dissolve. Cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast mixture and eggs.
Mix well. Gradually add the flour and salt, reserving a small amount of flour to dust raisins.
Add spices and floured raisins to the dough and knead in thoroughly.
Place in a buttered bowl; cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch the dough down and turn it out onto a floured board.
Shape dough into 30 buns and place on buttered cookie sheets.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes, then very carefully press the shape of a cross into each bun, using a spatula or the back of a knife.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until buns are browned, about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Frost either the entire bun or just the shape of the cross.

title: caramel apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cookie dough with flour and roll thin onto a pizza pan or baking stone.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Slide spatula under cookie dough.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
After first 10 minutes, stir and bake 5 to 10 minutes more. Store in zip-locked bag or airtight container when cooled.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: You also need mixing bowl, whisk, frying pan and spatula.

title: cabbage and casserole
directions: Steam chopped cabbage and onion.
In casserole, layer 1/2 of vegetables and 1/2 of soup, then remainder of cabbage and soup. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: 5 decker dinner
directions: Using 10-inch skillet (with lid), layer ingredients.

Cover skillet bottom with bacon, pat uncooked hamburger over bacon, add sliced onion layer, then green pepper slices (if family likes them), a little salt and pepper, thinly sliced carrots, top with thicker sliced potatoes (this ensures even cooking).
Add about 1 cup water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low about 45 to 60 minutes, basting with self-juice 2 to 3 times.
Bacon does not brown for eating, just adds flavor, also gives meat a pinkish look. Amounts may be adjusted according to personal tastes and skillet size.

title: italian beef
directions: Place both ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add reserved liquid and cook until tender.
Shred with fork.
Serve on Kaiser or onion roll.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil green peppers
for 10 minutes.
Remove tops from green peppers and dice into mixture of ground chuck, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Stuff peppers with ground chuck mixture.
Arrange in casserole dish and cover with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour, cheese, pepper and margarine.
Mix well. Shape small balls and press out with fork. Bake on ungreased baking pan at 325° for 20 minutes.
Can chill overnight and slice if you like.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: almond bark coconut drops
directions: Melt almond bark in a double boiler (warm water, not boiling). When melted, add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Take off heat; add peanuts or nuts, marshmallows, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Blend all of ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop by a spoonful on wax paper.
Let set for several hours.
Place in container between wax paper.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake into bars and frost.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until sugar melts or dissolves. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
If oven bakes fast, bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lost and found zucchini
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Transfer to casserole size baking dish or Pyrex lasagna dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: anytime burritos
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. (Break into small pieces.) Drain. Add refried beans and heat thoroughly. Heat shells in microwave until soft. Place by spoonfuls (in center of shells) sausage mixture. Fold on all four sides and place flaps down in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and place in oven on broil until cheese is melted. Serve warm. Salsa and sour cream can be eaten on top, if desired.

title: orange jelled salad
directions: Mix and dissolve the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 items and form into ball or log. Then roll in chopped pecans. These freeze well.

title: marsha's chicken nuggets
directions: Dice chicken.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown approximately 20 minutes in margarine in large skillet.
Put chicken in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Cover with broth, cheese and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: appetizer puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 5 ingredients.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal. Spread each rectangle with one tablespoon of mixture.
Starting at long side, roll up and seal edge.
Cut each roll into 8 to 10 pieces.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients over low heat until thick. Remove from heat; stir in the jello.
Cool and pour over sliced peaches.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Spread whipped cream on top, or serve with ice cream.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut chicken into cubes.
Boil broccoli.
Put chicken soup into bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheeses, then cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple joey
directions: Prepare cake according to box instructions; let cool.
Poke holes in top of cake.
Pour crushed pineapple over cake.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk; pour over cake.
Can be eaten now or frozen for 1 to 2 hours and served.

title: morning cookies
directions: In bowl, beat margarine (or butter) and brown sugar until well combined.
Add remaining ingredients (except raisins and nuts) and beat on low speed until combined.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Drop tablespoons of dough onto baking sheet and spread dough so each cookie is about 2-inches across.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until set.
