Cool. Spread bottom of half of the cookies with cream cheese or peanut butter and top with other halves.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Mix all together in top of a double boiler.
Put over gently boiling water and beat until smooth and thick.

title: cabbage cheese bake
directions: Cover cabbage with water in Dutch oven; bring water to a boil. Cook 2 1/2 minutes; drain well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over medium-low heat.
Blend in flour and paprika.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add cheese cubes; stir until melted.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Toss with cabbage and pour into large oblong baking dish.
Toss croutons with remaining melted margarine (2 tablespoons) and sprinkle over cabbage mixture. Cover and bake 25 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 20 minutes or until croutons are toasted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: perfect potato pancakes
directions: Peel and shred potatoes; place in a bowl of cold water. Line a colander with cheesecloth or a clean thin dish towel.
Drain potatoes into cloth and squeeze out as much moisture as possible. Place potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Beat eggs; add to potatoes along with onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat about 1/3 cup salad oil in a skillet until hot.
Drop potato mixture 1/4 cup at a time into hot oil, about 3 inches apart.
Flatten with pancake turner to make a 4-inch pancake.
Cook pancakes until golden brown; turn and cook other side, about 4 minutes total.
Remove to a cookie sheet lined with paper towel to drain.
Repeat until all pancakes are cooked.
Serve immediately or place in a warm oven until ready to serve.
Top with maple syrup or applesauce.
Yield: About 16 pancakes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread cherry pie filling in pan.
In small bowl, combine oats, flour and brown sugar.
With 2 knives, work in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; sprinkle evenly over cherry filling.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until topping is lightly browned.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, carrots and onion in oleo.
Place in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Add croutons.
Mix soup and cream cheese; pour on top and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave herb potatoes
directions: Make crosswise cuts, 1/2-inch apart in each potato, not cutting all the way through.
Place an onion slice in each cut.
Place potatoes in 2-quart microwavable casserole.
Cover and microwave on High until potatoes are almost tender for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix well. Pour in greased pie dish.
Spread. Save enough to sprinkle on top.
Put the rhubarb on top.

title: honey banana bread(no cholesterol)
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add walnuts.
Combine bananas, lemon juice, honey and milk.
Add flour mixture a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg white. Pour into lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add one cup of sugar gradually and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff and shiny.
Place in a greased pie plate or one large shell sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Put egg yolks in a double boiler; heat until thick.
Add 1 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind; cook stirring until thick, 5 or 8 minutes. Beat cream.
Mix 1/2 with cooled lemon custard.
Place in a cool pie shell and top with your topping.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Pour yeast in a big bowl and add water; stir. Add butter and sugar; mix well.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour and mix well. Put in refrigerator. Let dough rise for several hours before using; overnight works real well. Dough can be kept in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 24 rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin pans 1/2 full.

title: 3-6-9-icing
directions: Boil butter, cream and brown sugar until it bubbles. Add vanilla and enough powdered sugar to spread well. Beat.

title: carrot roast
directions: Mix peanut butter with water.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dr. bird's cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer!
Blend with spoon.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, until all are well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured stem pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Place foil over top of cake for 20 minutes more (while cooling).

title: ham sauce
directions: Mix together and cover ham.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix ingredients, then pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift together into a bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon. Add to sifted mixture the brown sugar, shortening and buttermilk or sour milk. Beat all together vigorously for about 2 minutes. Add 3 medium unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, nuts and flour which has been sifted with soda and salt.
Place in 2 bread pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
This is good to cool and freeze in foil.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir gently to mix.
Spoon into 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: coconut, pecan, pineapple pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add drained pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Mix well. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana raspberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except preserves and pour into two 9-inch pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° until done. Ice with buttercream icing.
Put raspberry preserves in between layers and on top.

title: pumpkin tomato chutney
directions: Peel pumpkin, discard seeds and scrape out center.
Slice and cut into 2 x 1 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel and slice tomatoes.
Peel and slice onions and press garlic.
Crush peppercorns and allspice in a mortar.
Put all ingredients in large pan.
Bring gently to a boil.
Cook very slowly and stir often.
When jammy, put into jars.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 2 qt. casserole in microwave.
Saute onion in melted butter for 3 minutes.
Combine corn chips and most of the cheese, chili, beans, and corn.
Microwave 9 minutes on high, turning periodically.
Add the rest of the cheese when almost done.

title: sassy zucchini
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off excess fat.
In large Dutch oven, add browned beef, onions and all other ingredients together.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until rice is done and vegetables are soft.
If too soupy, add 3 teaspoons flour.

title: hearty vegetable soup(crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except frozen vegetables, in cooker. Cook on low 10 to 11 hours. Add frozen vegetables and heat it through. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: georgia's shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream, Hidden Valley dressing mix and drained and mashed shrimp well. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add soup mixture.
Add carrots.
Let set overnight.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; add diced apples.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to the apple mix. Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: coconut-orange cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and milk.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hot cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in scooped out loaf with top. Wrap in foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cool slightly.
Dice potatoes and drizzle some olive oil over them.
When cool, add onions to potatoes and coat with Ranch dressing to taste.
Garnish with dill.

title: vegetable parmesan
directions: Add all vegetables in a large casserole dish.
Add garlic, spaghetti sauce and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, crushed corn flakes, parsley flakes, 2 eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion.
Form meat balls and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, heat cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice until melted.
Pour over meat balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red cucumber pickles(mock apple rings)
directions: Peel, core and slice cucumbers 1/2-inch thick.
Take 1 gallon water and 1 cup lime; mix well and pour over cucumbers in churn. Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Wash 3 times.
Drain.
Cover with ice and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Take 1 cup white vinegar, red cake coloring, alum and enough water to cover.
Simmer for 2 hours. Drain.
Throw this liquid away.
Take 4 cups white vinegar, cinnamon sticks, sugar, 4 cups water and red hots.
Boil for 40 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and heat liquid until hot.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand again.
Third morning, heat in pan for a few minutes until hot and put in jars and seal.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Put into a baking dish.
Melt the 1/3 cup margarine.
Add sugar, flour, pecans and coconut.
Put on top of sweet potatoes and squash mix.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dump in cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Place cut up margarine over cake mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pulao(pilaf)
directions: Wash the rice twice and leave aside.
Heat the oil in a pot. Add cardamon, cloves and peppercorns.
Fry for about 1
minute. Add rice and stir-fry for a further 2 minutes.
Add salt and water; lower heat.
(At this point, you may add chickpeas or green peas if you wish.)
Cover and simmer over a very low heat until water has evaporated.

title: lyenda's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add and mix sour cream and baking powder.
Alternate dry ingredients and sour cream.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a floured, lightly greased flute pan.

title: pasta with sausage and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: First:
Cook sausage in microwave (6 minutes on High) or by steaming in a covered pan over medium-low heat until cooked.
Cut sausage into small, bite-sized pieces.
Reserve.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Brown roast on both sides in large dutch oven.
Combine onion, brown sugar, salt, pepper, ginger, cloves, allspice, bay leaf, 1 c. water and vinegar.
Mix well and pour over roast. Cover and simmer or bake at 325° 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until tender, turning over roast once.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir 1/2 c. water into flour then stir into pan drippings. Cook, stirring constantly.
Add water, if needed.
Makes great gravy.
Serve with "lots" of mashed potatoes.

title: tasty quick spinach
directions: Place drained spinach in a small saucepan and add all other ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Heat spinach until boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: granny's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix up with spoon or hands.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes then slice.

title: broccoli cheddar noodle bake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan or dish.
In large bowl, stir in Cheddar cheese, sour cream, broccoli, green onion, mayonnaise and salt until blended.
Add noodles; toss to coat.
Spoon into prepared baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter corn flake cookies
directions: Boil sugar and Karo for 1 minute.
Mix peanut butter and corn flakes, then put by spoon onto wax paper.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Brown in oil and drain well.

title: tuna cheese elbow
directions: Cook macaroni and drain with cold water.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together, then add spices to macaroni.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well with enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: hamburger helper homestyle
directions: Brown the beef, salt and pepper in a skillet.
Add the onion, celery, peas and tomatoes.
While beef is browning, cook in salty water the noodles.
Drain noodles and spread over meat mixture. Sprinkle the cheese over all.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes to blend flavors. Serve from skillet.

title: prune cake(tastes like a spice cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl in order listed.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread out crescent roll dough on 10 x 13-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley Ranch and mayonnaise, dill weed, pepper and garlic salt.
Place mixture over crescent rolls. Sprinkle chopped veggies over top of cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of veggies.
Gently pat down. Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix well and keep in a cool place.
(I keep mine in the refrigerator in a jar.)

title: chewy caramels
directions: Combine all ingredients but 1 cup milk and vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Stir in milk slowly so as not to stop boiling.
Boil to fairly firm, hard ball or 250°.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; pour into buttered 3/4-inch pan.
Cool, then cut.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
(Make sure skillet is already hot.) Add shrimp to brown, then the onion.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add egg and cooked rice.
Mix.
Add seasonings to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Ready to serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix; let stand overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables of your choice.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Place the evaporated milk in the freezer for at least one hour.
Beat the evaporated milk at high speed until it doubles its volume.
Add the sweetened condensed milk slowly, beating at medium speed.
Add the lemon juice slowly, beating at medium speed, until the mixture gets harder.
Place in the refrigerator. Decorate with maraschino cherries or any topping you like.

title: shrimp curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate overnight. Serve cold with veggies.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in saucepot.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Do not cook.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Put cocoa, vinegar and cake coloring in cup and mix well; add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Add flour, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350°.

title: apple filling
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan; cook and stir until smooth.
Add apples and cinnamon and cook until apples are tender.
Place suitable amount in unbaked pie crust. Top with butter slices, another pie crust, and bake at 400° until done.
* You can make pies, wrap completely with foil and freeze.
To bake, thaw at room temperature or refrigerator and bake as usual.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Boil potatoes in thin jackets for 20 minutes; cool.
Peel and cut into thick slices.
Lay in greased casserole dish.
Make sauce by mixing sugars, cornstarch and orange juice.
Let come to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat, add oleo and pour over potatoes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles until soft; drain thoroughly.
Beat the eggs until frothy.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking pan and place it into a cold oven.
Turn the oven onto 350° and bake for one hour.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press in 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts into dough.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs together and pour over first mixture.
Sprinkle with another cup of chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream squash
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Bring 2 cups of water to a boil; add squash, salt and sugar. Cover saucepan and cook over moderate
heat
20	minutes
or until tender.
Meanwhile, melt 4 tablespoons
of
butter
in a small skillet.
Add onion and cook until
transparent;
set aside.
When squash is done, drain, pressing to
force out
excess
liquid.
Stir onion and butter into the
squash.
One at a time, add the Cheddar, sour cream, Romano, white wine and salt and pepper to taste, mixing thoroughly after
each
addition.
Pour
mixture
into a large casserole or individual ramekins.

title: ortega fiesta bake
directions: Grease 8 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch casserole.
Line casserole with peppers, opened flat.
Add grated cheese.
Beat eggs and sour cream mixture and pour over cheese.
Top with layer of peppers (opened flat).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out.
Remove from oven and let cool a few minutes to set.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix well.
Place in a well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 350° for 1 hour or until firm and deep brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, folding in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Place mixture into a well-greased, crumbled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot and spicy tex-mex muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine all ingredients except cornmeal mix.
Add cornmeal mix and blend well.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 to almost full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit and add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Boil and add to gelatins to dissolve. Stir in orange sherbet. Pour into 6 cup mold. Chill until partially set and fold in fruit. Chill until firm. Garnish with mint leaves and mayonnaise and serve with chicken or pork. Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Wash elephant and cut into bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook slowly at 465° about 4 weeks.
Yields 4,000 servings.
If more people are expected the rabbits may be added, but only if needed, as some people do not like hare in their soup.

title: bran cherry loaf
directions: Mix cereal and milk.
Let stand until soft.
Stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add egg and oil to cereal mixture; beat well.
Add flour mixture and stir well.
Fold in chopped cherries (reserving 2 tablespoons chopped cherries for topping) and 3/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut and walnuts in large bowl.
Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Stir until it boils.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla. Pour over oatmeal mixture.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: dry roux
directions: Put flour in cast-iron skillet or Dutch oven.
Bake at 400° until dark brown.
Stir occasionally.
Store leftover dry roux in a tightly capped Mason jar in the refrigerator.

title: anise drops
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 30 minutes.
Time is important. Add flour and anise and blend well.
Drop from spoon to a greased cookie sheet and decorate with colored sugar. Do not press down. Cover with wax paper and let stand over night.
Bake at 300° about 15 minutes.
Store in tight can with 1 apple for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add the five dry ingredients.
Add the zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix and bake in 2 loaf pans or in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spanish soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan, add onion and cook for 2-3 min. Add potatoes and cook for 1-2 min. Stir broth into pan, season with salt, pepper bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 10 min. Add sausage and corn. Bring to boil then simmer for 10 more min. Stir in oregano then pour into bowls. Serve with tortillas.

title: deviled food cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; then sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together 2 or 3 times.
Cream Crisco, sugar, egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix dry and creamed mixtures and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and milk; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat and add oats, peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir well and drop onto wax paper by spoon.
Then let cool.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients in blender.
Mix with rest of ingredients.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar, then stir in grapes. Place grape mixture in dish and top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Refrigerate.

title: work day roast
directions: Place roast in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut slots in roast and place cut up fresh garlic.
Pour soup over roast and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over this and salt and pepper.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Place in oven at 250°.
Bake from 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.
Roast will be ready and the gravy made.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil together tomato soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper for 15 minutes and cool. Mix with carrots, onion and pepper.
Set overnight.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.

title: baked wisconsin brie
directions: Place cheese on ovenproof serving plate.
Saute almonds and garlic in butter until just browned.
Pour over top of Brie.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until warmed through (in microwave 3 to 5 minutes).
Serve with sliced French bread or fruit (sliced apples).

title: earl's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour in medium sauce pan.
Stir in egg yolks, milk, water and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Then add next 3.
Mix thoroughly. Place in unbaked pie shell and cook 50 minutes at 325°.

title: easy chicken dumplings
directions: Put chicken in large boiler.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pour chicken broth into a separate pan to use later.
Pull chicken off bone.
Place into boiler.
Add chicken broth, cream of chicken soup, boiled eggs, salt, pepper and butter.
Let simmer while preparing biscuits.

title: cream puff cake
directions: In a saucepan, put 1 stick of margarine; add 1 cup water and 1 cup flour.
Stir over heat until it comes together like a ball. Put in a bowl; beat in 4 eggs, adding one at a time.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let stand.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with corn chips.
Can be frozen.

title: delicious chicken breasts
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for 1 more hour.

title: tabouli(greek salad)
directions: Mix bulgar, boiling water and salt in pan. Cover and let stand 20 to 30 minutes or until bulgar is chewable (water is absorbed). Add lemon juice, garlic, oil, mint and pepper.
Mix and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add veggies before serving.
Add cheese and mix. (Salt may be omitted since the cheese is salty.)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Thaw carrots in cold water, drain and pat dry. Mix rest of ingredients. Pour over carrots and let stand, refrigerated, overnight or for 24 hours. Stir once or twice while they marinate. These keep well. They may be served as an appetizer or salad rather than a vegetable dish.

title: glazed cereal
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook 6 to 8 minutes; should boil about 2 minutes, then add vanilla and soda.
Pour this over Crispix and party nuts in a large bowl.
Stir and transfer to a large paper bag which has been sprayed inside with Pam.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; shake.
Microwave 1 minute; shake.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Cool and break apart.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into small balls; roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove; press chocolate kisses (or stars) into center of each cookie.
Press so cookie cracks.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: moravian chicken pies
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Break up 1 pie shell and place in bottom of dish.
Crumble chicken on top of shell. Melt butter into soup plus 2 cups chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble 2nd pie shell on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: appetizer hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Chill canned fruit before mixing.
Drain fruit; slice bananas. Add strawberries and pie filling.
Mix together and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add salt and pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Cook noodles.
Combine onions, sour cream, cottage cheese and noodles.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Place meat in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on Full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Combine tomato sauce, taco seasoning mix, beans and olives.
Spoon mixture over 2 cups of chips in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on Full power for 5 minutes.
Slightly crush remaining chips.
Sprinkle casserole with chips and cheese.
Heat on Full power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and sweeten to taste, 3 1/2 to 4 cups sugar.
Serve over crushed ice.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: pear honey
directions: Pare, core and chop pears; cover with enough water to cook. Boil for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, sugar, juice and rind and ginger.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars, seal with paraffin.

title: maw maw's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into a ball and place on a floured board or counter top.
Knead a few times, then roll out and use cookie cutter for cutting.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: Combine pecans, sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart bowl and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Add butter and vanilla and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy and spread quickly onto greased cookie sheet.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute onion, celery and herbs (parsley and fennel) in 3 tablespoons of butter for 3 minutes.
Add the watercress and spinach.
Cook until these green vegetables wilt. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining butter to the bread crumbs, liqueur and seasonings (salt, pepper and red pepper).
Set aside.

title: fish au gratin
directions: Brush fillets with mayonnaise.
Mix cheese and crumbs.
Roll fish in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily with fork.

title: sloppy joes 1
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly until vegetables are tender.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together the cornstarch, sugar and cold water in small pan.
Cook on medium to high until it turns clear.
Stir constantly.
Add jello.
Let cool, but not gel.
Put strawberries in the pie crust.
Pour jello mixture over strawberries and refrigerate until gelled.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Mix egg yolks and remaining ingredients together in order listed.
Beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Combine first three ingredients and pat in the bottom of pan (greased pan).
Combine other ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip the marshmallow cream, cream cheese and honey until smooth and creamy. Good with slices of apples, bananas, peaches, strawberries or oranges.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer beat brown sugar, oil and egg until mixed.
Add flour and milk a little at a time with mixer on low and alternating the two.
Add rest of dry ingredients. Continue to beat on low until well mixed.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on racks before removing.
Wrap and store overnight in refrigerator to develop flavor.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine Hawaiian Fruit Punch, fruit juice concentrates and water.
Pour over ice in a large punch bowl.
Resting bowl on rim of large punch bowl, carefully pour ginger ale down side.
Mix gently with up and down motion.
Trim with fresh fruit slices. Makes 30 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix crackers and 2 melted sticks margarine in baking dish for crust.
Press firmly in dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool. Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread in crust. Blend potatoes with 3/4 stick margarine, vanilla, 3/4 cup sugar, egg and salt until smooth.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.

title: chocolate taffy
directions: Cook water, chocolate, sugar, molasses and butter together until the syrup forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water. Add vanilla and pour into a buttered pan to cool and harden.
When stiff, mark off in squares with a knife.
When cold and brittle, break off on marked squares.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Heat cooking oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is yellow.
Add venison and cook until browned.
In another skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and cook until they have absorbed the butter and just start to give it up.
Add to venison.
Stir in all other ingredients except flour and water.
Reduce heat to low and cook 2 hours.
Stir together flour and water.
Stir into venison and let cook 10 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: doggie liver biscuits
directions: Cut liver into small pieces and grind in food processor.
Put in bowl and add cornmeal, flour and garlic powder.
Mix well. Spread liver mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread out to edges of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Refrigerate when cool.
Your dog will love you forever if you make this treat!

title: greek sauce
directions: Cook hamburg and drain.
Simmer hamburg and onions until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 3 hours. Use to top hamburgers or hot dogs.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; pat into cakes and fry.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and margarine together.
Pat into an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs, blending well. Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour can of blueberry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: plum pork stir-fry
directions: In a wok or large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add pork and stir-fry over high heat until cooked through, 5 to 6 minutes. Remove pork to a plate.

Add onion and green pepper to drippings in wok and stir-fry just until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in plums, jam, lemon juice, brown sugar, mustard and ginger. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Mix cornstarch and water until blended.
Stir into sauce and cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Return pork to skillet and simmer 1 to 2 minutes, until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: chalet ham dip
directions: Thoroughly combine first four ingredients.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Serve as a dip for Swiss cheese crackers.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups dip.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat; season.
Drain if needed.
Mix soup, tomato and peppers with meat.
Layer with tortillas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture and repeat.
Make cheese last on top.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serve with Mexican Salad.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and bean dip; add diced onion.
Make into a ring or ball.
Pour on sauce.
Top with grated cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: soup o' salad
directions: Heat oven on 350° for 5 minutes.
Mix batter.
Grease pan. Pour batter into pan.
Cook until done.
Let cool.
Put whipped cream on top of cake.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use ice ring for garnish in punch bowl.
Serves 25.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Measure flour into a bowl by spooning into measuring cup and leveling off.
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk with a fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut without twisting cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes about 12 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts with fork.
Melt all ingredients together in a large skillet.
Serve hot/warm.

title: creme de menthe mold
directions: Line a 5 1/2 cup ring mold with wax paper or Saran and then with ladyfingers rounded side out.
Beat sherbet and creme de menthe until smooth, but not melted.
Spoon into mold.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold and fill center with strawberries.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers, celery and salt.
Let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric in saucepan; bring to a boil, then let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Store in glass gallon jar in refrigerator.
These keep a long time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Place in glass casserole dish.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot on grater in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
After thoroughly mixed, add to cabbage and carrot; mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: carrot pudding boats
directions: Line a buttered one-quart casserole dish with sliced bread. Combine the egg yolks, milk, nutmeg, salt, sugar and carrots.

title: fried hominy
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Simmer onions, celery, bell pepper and red pepper until tender.
Add hominy.
Cook until slightly brown. Add salt, black pepper and crumbled bacon.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook
onions and pepper until onions are
yellow
in
3 tablespoons
butter.
Add ground beef until
lightly
browned. Stir in cooked tomatoes, uncooked rice,
chili powder, pepper, salt
and tomato sauce.
Pour into	greased
casserole;
cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Grind cheese and nuts together.
Mix in garlic buds and Tabasco.
Sprinkle paprika on waxed paper.
Shape cheese mixture into log shape and roll in paprika.
Chill.
Makes about 2 (8-inch) logs.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and carrot. Butter dish.
Line with Ritz crackers.
Add squash mixture and top with crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: hidden apple coffee cake
directions: Grease pan.
Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon in bowl. Separate biscuits and dip into melted butter, then into sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits, putting apple slice between each biscuit.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 400° or until brown.
Cool upright in pan for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar, vanilla and milk and beat until smooth.
Drizzle over cake.
Yields 10 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add coffee and beans, then cool. Add brandy. Cap bottle and let sit for 30 days. Stir weekly. Makes 1 gallon.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Let stand 30 minutes, serve.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Mix ham, mustard and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread and cut into desired shapes.

title: simply scrumptious
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, sour cream, shredded cheese and 1/2 can French fried onion rings together.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining French fried onion rings on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until bubbly; serve hot.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and mace.
In mixer bowl beat together 1/2 cup sugar, cooking oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Gradually add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Fill 10 greased muffin tins 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tops are firm and brown.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix together and cook to hard ball stage.
Pour on greased (butter) marble slab.
Add drops of coloring and oil of peppermint.
Fold in edges enough to hold in hands.
Pull mints until hard and glossy.
Cut with scissors to desired sizes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut into 1/4-inch rings.
Heat oil 1-inch deep in large skillet.
Beat milk, flour, salt and baking powder by hand or with mixer until smooth.
Make sure batter is thick.
Dip each onion ring in batter; fry a few at a time.
Try to turn only once.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Place ribs or stew beef in a large clay cooker or roasting pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake (covered) at 350° for 3 to 4 hours (or until meat is tender).

title: rhubarb orange jello jam
directions: Cook on low heat until tender.
Add 1 package orange Jell-O. Put in jars and freeze.
A very tasty jam.

title: miso soup(japanese soup)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in sesame oil for 10 minutes.
Add a dash of ginger.
Cut up carrot, burdock and daiken and add to onion
mixture.
Stir while cooking for 5 minutes.
Add 5 cups water and bring to a boil; slow boil for 7 or 8 minutes, then add 1 tablespoon miso.
Cut up zucchini and mushrooms (caps only) and add to mixture.
Simmer 8 minutes, then add the tofu and the other tablespoon of miso.
Add a dash of cayenne pepper; stir well and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook
potatoes	 before
other
ingredients.	Combine margarine and onions in 2 quart casserole.	Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or cook on top
of	stove
until
onions
are clear. Stir in broth, salt and	pepper.
Cook until broth is boiling. Add potatoes, milk and	cream.	Cook until piping hot.	Serves 4.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Melt over hot water. When melted, remove from heat and stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool thoroughly.
Will keep well in cool place for 3 weeks, if they last that long.

title: western taters
directions: According to your preference, you may or may not peel the potatoes. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put into bowl.
Pour one tablespoon olive oil over potato chunks.
Stir.
Sprinkle seasoning over potatoes.
Stir.
Place on cookie sheet in single layer.
Place in 375° oven.
Cook 20 minutes.
Turn chunks.
Cook 20 minutes longer if crisp texture is desired.
Serve similar as French fries, low sodium, low fat.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Chop nuts rather coarsely and set aside.
Work or cream butter or margarine and shortening together until smooth.
Then beat in confectioners' sugar gradually.
Stir in flour thoroughly and add vanilla extract and nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until a delicate light brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and bananas. Mix.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans or sheet cake pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cooked dressing
directions: Cook the sugar, vinegar, eggs, salt, butter and mustard until thick.
Stir in the cream.

title: company rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook, covered, at 350° until rice is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan-crumble sweet potatoes
directions: Combine flour, sugar and allspice; mix well.
Cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Spray 2 quart dish with PAM.
Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Place 1 layer of potatoes in dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Layer remaining slices, overlapping.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and pecans.
Drizzle maple syrup on top.
Bake at 350 degrees, lightly covered with foil, for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 10 minutes.

title: baked apples in orange sauce
directions: Pare and cut each apple into 4 pieces.
Arrange in buttered baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Add orange juice and water.
Pour this mixture over the arranged apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Serves 6.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, cracker crumbs and almonds; sprinkle over vegetables. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all and mix.
(Drain liquid from onion and peppers.)
Mix sugar and spices.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes or to desired thickness.

title: butter-pecan ice cream pie
directions: Blend milk and ice cream in bowl.
Add pie mix (instant pudding); beat
about
3 minutes.
Pour into crust and chill 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip.
Real good.

title: turkey-rice soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Add rice and carrots; cover and simmer an additional 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Remove bay leaf.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pineapple carrot cake(from:   "southern living" cookbook)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Dust lightly with flour; tap out excess.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.

Make a well in the center and add in order: sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat with wooden spoon until smooth. Stir in carrots, coconut, walnuts and pineapple until well blended; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
(Center will sink slightly.)
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Spread with cream cheese frosting.
Loaded with calories, but worth every one.

title: southwestern style soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain. Mix rest of ingredients; bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve with Fritos, corn chips and sour cream, salsa, etc.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Place in the top pan of a double boiler.
Beat with hand held electric mixer for 1 minute to mix thoroughly.
Make sure water is boiling.
Beat at high speed for 7 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread on a medium size cake.

title: mazetti(very good ground beef casserole)
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soups.
Add noodles, garlic salt, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale last.
Drop scoops of vanilla ice cream on top of punch.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and cocoa; bring to a rolling boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet or wax paper and let set until hard.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine jello, strawberries, water and pineapple and pour in flat glass dish or jello mold 1/2 of the mixture.
Refrigerate to set.
When jello sets, spread sour cream across top, then pour second half of jello mixture over it and return to refrigerator. (Looks nicer in mold disk.)

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese in the mixer, then add crushed pineapple and pineapple ice cream topping. Add about 1/4 to 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Mix together well. Roll into a large ball, then roll in crushed pecans. Make holes in top of ball and dribble pineapple ice cream topping into holes. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: wieners in corn bread
directions: Mix muffin mix according to directions on the box.
Pour into a greased oblong 6 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Slice wieners through the middle not cutting them all the way.
Fill each wiener with mustard and 1 teaspoon pickle relish.
Place wieners on top of muffin mix lengthwise a few inches apart.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Slice between each wiener.
Serve 6 slices.

title: diabetic loaf cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 1/2 hours in loaf pan coated with butter or Pam at 300°.
After cake is cool, wrap in foil to prevent drying out.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine onion, broccoli, eggs, margarine, cottage cheese and salt in a bowl; mix well. Add muffin mix; stir just until moistened. Spoon into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields: 12 servings.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk, then roll in crumbs.
Line shallow baking pan with foil.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
May also remove skin before dipping.

title: chicken elegance casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and salt and pepper.
Cook chicken (save broth); cut into pieces.
Mix until smooth mushroom soup and sour cream.
Put into casserole.
Heat 1 cup chicken broth; add 1 tablespoon butter with sauteed celery and onions to stuffing mix. Spread filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley.
Brush butter on one side of bread slice.
Place bread in napkin-lined basket or plate and bake in oven until lightly brown.
Delicious served with spaghetti.

title: sue's stuffed jalapenos
directions: Cut jalapenos in half lengthwise, remove seeds, wash and dry. Prepare 1/2 bag stuffing as directed.
Add shrimp and crabmeat to stuffing.
If desired, add 1/4 teaspoon each salt and cayenne pepper, or to taste.
Stuff peppers full, batter and brown in a small amount of oil over medium heat.
I like to use egg (beaten) with ice water or milk, then roll in cracker meal.
Enjoy!!

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour smoothly.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Stir in the cheese and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Add seasonings.
Cool slightly.
Beat in egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake in a 375° oven until souffle is puffed and brown (30 to 35 minutes).
Serve at once. Serves 4.

title: bloomin' onion
directions: Select a well-rounded onion.
Peel outer skin off.
Leave root intact.
Cut off any hanging roots.
Using small, sharp knife, divide onion into four sections by making 2 cuts crosswise, beginning at the top and cutting toward root, stopping about 1/2-inch away.
Cut each section twice.
Place onion in bowl of enough boiling water to cover it and leave for 5 minutes.
The sections or "petals" will begin to open.
Remove onion from hot water and immerse into ice water to help the opening.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef in fat.
Add garlic, onion, pepper and chili powder. Stir to blend well.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beans and rice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 8.

title: overnight oven cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Add pinch of cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in 2/3 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Fold in chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Place by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place pan in oven.
Turn off oven and leave overnight.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Pam a 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread berries on paper towel to dry.
Combine brown sugar and flour.
Add berries; turn into baking dish.
Prepare topping.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together including the egg white.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Stays soft and fluffy and can be stored in refrigerator.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and condensed milk together.
Pour into pie shells and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dip thawed fish in milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: In a large bowl, empty 2 bags oyster crackers. Mix oil, seasoned salt, Hidden Valley, dill weed and shake well. Pour evenly over crackers and stir. Coat well and evenly. Spread on two large cookie sheets and bake at 200° about 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: velvet chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add beaten eggs then melted chocolate.
Beat after each.
Mix alternately flour and water and beat after each addition.
Then add the dissolved soda last.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, cook celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Add 4 1/2 cups milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, carrots, potatoes and peas.
Remove from heat.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender and translucent. Add the corn, potatoes, chicken broth and herbs. Simmer for 25 minutes. Add the milk, butter and check the seasonings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from racks and cool completely.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Add together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips, walnuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, spice packet and water. Blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Fry 1/2 pound hot
sausage.
Blot
grease.
Set
aside. Bake pie shell for
minutes
Set aside.
Dip each tomato slice
in
cup flour seasoned with salt and coarse pepper. Saute
tomatoes quickly in 2 tablespoons cooking oil. Set aside. Arrange
cup
sliced olives and 2 tablespoons minced onions in bottom of cooked pie shell.
Add the following
ingredients
in layers:
Swiss
cheese, sausage, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes.
Stir together 2 slightly beaten eggs and 1 cup half and	half.
Pour over mixture and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: crown jewel pie
directions: Prepare one package of gelatin using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill in 8-inch square pan until firm. Dissolve remaining gelatin and sugar in 1 cup boiling water; add pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened; blend in whipped cream.
Cut firm gelatin into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fold into cream mixture, reserving a few for garnish.
Chill until mixture mounds. Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with cubes and more whipped cream.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add oats and vanilla and corn syrup. Mix well.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter. Spread over slightly cooled squares.
Cut and refrigerate.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add tomatoes and Chili-O mix. Add water, then stir. Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Add salad oil, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Sift together, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix into apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Serve with flavored whipped topping.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
In large skillet, saute the onion in butter until golden.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Add seasonings, flour, mushrooms and consomme.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in sour cream.

title: holiday shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill; serve with crackers.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, then put all of the ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tiger butter(candy)
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter on top of double boiler over HOT NOT BOILING water.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered sheet pan 10x15 with sides.
Tap pan to distribute mixture.
In top of same double boiler melt dark or semi-sweet chocolate.
With a teaspoon drizzle dark chocolate over white chocolate in stripes about 1 inch apart.
Using a table knife swirl back and forth through dark and white chocolate to create "tiger stripes."

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in milk, orange juice and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 9 to 10 dozen.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and pecan chips; cover and chill one hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in pecan pieces.
Cover and chill.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen balls.

title: cherry punch
directions: Put one pound regular grind coffee in cheesecloth or muslin bag which is large enough to hold twice that amount to allow for circulation.
Drop bag into two gallons of boiling water.
Cover tightly and reduce heat; let stand 6 to 10 minutes.
Remove bag; keep coffee hot for serving.

title: lemon yum yum
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Make into balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter, add onions, celery, bell pepper and flour.
Cover and saute for about 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cover and cook another 20 minutes.
Add cream cheese, jalapeno peppers and garlic; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, on low for another 20 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Dry breasts; sprinkle with salt.
Mix flour in sour cream; add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Do not cover.

title: baked ziti with three cheeses
directions: Cook pasta following package directions; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl blend Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, parsley, garlic, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in ziti.
Spoon into prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake until top is golden, about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: burger and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in a small amount of fat.
Salt and pepper.
Add all the rest except beans, cornbread batter and grated cheese; simmer 10 minutes (no water).
Turn heat off and add 1 can of drained kidney beans.
Put in casserole.
Top with cornbread batter and grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: daddy's potato soup
directions: Add all to a large pot. Dice and fry the bacon. Drain and add to pot. Cook, uncovered, very slowly for 30 minutes or until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook on stove to melt. Do not boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla and oats.
Stir together. Spoon out onto greased cookie pan or waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; add cheese and corn.
Fry bacon; put half in mix and other on top.

title: crab soup
directions: Mix all soups together, then add milk, curry and crab.
Heat through and serve with good French bread.
This is great!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; roll in extra sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with floured potato masher or fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, buttermilk, prunes and
nuts.
Mix
flour,
spices, baking powder, baking soda and salt
and
add to other mixture.
(If too stiff, add more buttermilk.)
Pour into greased and floured pans (either two 9-inch
pans
or
one
x
13-inch
pan).
Bake about 25 minutes at 350° or until tester comes out clean.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion until meat is browned.
Add next 9 ingredients and cook at least 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix together cornstarch and water, stirring until smooth.
Add to chili and cook about 15 minutes longer before serving.

title: "mock apple pie"
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil; boil for 1 minute. Drop the Ritz crackers or soda crackers into liquid; press into liquid.
Do not stir.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place the butter (small pats) all over top of pie. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with other crisscrossed crust.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: salmon appetizer
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones.
In small bowl, combine salmon, cream cheese, salsa, parsley and cilantro.
Add cumin, if desired. Spread about 2 tablespoons of the salmon mixture over each tortilla.
Roll tortilla up tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Slice into bite-size pieces.
Yields about 48 appetizers.

title: blueberry lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in lemon rind.
Dredge blueberries in 2 teaspoons of flour.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
cake and jello. Add eggs, water, and oil. Mix well. Thaw strawberries and fold in 1/2
box juice and strawberries. Bake at 350 for 40 - 50 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Wipe pork chops with a damp cloth.
Make a few slits at the fat side of each pork chop.
Place in glass pan or stainless bowl.

title: apple butter pie
directions: In a bowl, combine apple butter, egg, sugar, flour and milk; mix well.
Pour into the pie shell; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°; bake 35 minutes more or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sensibly delicious chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Cream sugars, butter and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute celery, onion, bell pepper and ground beef in Dutch oven.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
After it cools, skim the fat off the top.

title: apple cake
directions: Slice apples, put on bottom of pan, sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar mixed. Mix in bowl 1 cup sugar, eggs, oil, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on apples.
Spread and sprinkle a little cinnamon and sugar mixture on top.
(If still doughy, just cover with foil and continue baking a few more minutes.)
If larger pan is used, multiply recipe by 1 1/2.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a saucepan; saute onion and garlic.
Stir in 1/4 cup ripe olives, green chiles, sour cream and soup; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this sauce; set aside. Fold in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese.

title: slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over cabbage. Mix well.
You may add chopped carrots, green pepper and chopped onions.
If using less cabbage, use less vinegar, oil and sugar, but use equal amounts of each.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in 5-quart Dutch oven until partially cooked.
Brown beef in bacon drippings.
Remove and pour off drippings.
Return beef and bacon to Dutch oven.
Stir in wine, carrots, marjoram, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add onion and small amount of vinegar.
Add oil gradually.
Add celery seed.
Add dash of paprika for coloring.
Beat until thick.
(I put mine in the blender.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with raw cut up vegetables.

title: rice krispies
directions: Heat
sugar
and
corn syrup to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: three cup shortcake
directions: Bake in an iron skillet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Split and use whatever fruit you like, such as strawberries, peaches, etc.
Top with Cool Whip and slice like you would a pie.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Add about 1 to 1 1/2 pounds raw shrimp.
Coat evenly.
Drop shrimp in hot oil and fry until browned.
Shrimp stay moist with crispy outside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion in a small amount of water for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, mix carrot, sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Drain zucchini and fold into carrot mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine; add herb stuffing mix, then mix.
Layer a casserole dish with 1/2 stuffing mix; add zucchini mixture and top with remaining stuffing. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry angel(serves 16)
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries (sweetened), stirring occasionally.
When berries are thawed and mixture begins to thicken, add whipping cream (I used 16 ounce size whipped topping).

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add honey, lemon juice and vinegar.
Blend.
Gradually beat salad oil into mixture.
Yields 2 cups.

title: spinach casserole 1
directions: Cook spinach; squeeze out excess water.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes at 350° in lightly covered casserole.

title: ham casserole
directions: Arrange the first 2 items in casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Add to casserole with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar.
Melt butter and add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add milk slowly.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, cereal and margarine; roll into balls.
In a double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolates. Add vanilla.
Dip balls in melted chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in saucepan until spins definite thread.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Beat with spoon while pouring syrup, then beat with mixer until stands in peaks, then beat with spoon until loses gloss.
Add vanilla and 1 cup nuts. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut cinnamon buns into squares.
Combine bun cubes with milk and cream in a large bowl. Set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs and almond extract.
Add to bread mixture. Add walnuts, raisins and chopped apricots. Spoon into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 325° until firm, 50 minutes.
Serve hot or room temperature with Cool Whip or whipped cream on top.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat Coke and dissolve jello.
Add pineapple juice and stir. Let set until almost thick.
Add pineapple, pecans and cream cheese.
Stir up and rejell.

title: chocolate swirl cake
directions: Put coconut and walnuts in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cake mix over this.
Heat together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until soft.
Drop in creamed mixture. Swirl with knife to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Soft on top; poke with toothpick to test.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Form a pan out of aluminum foil large enough to put 6 boneless chicken breasts in.
Pour Wickers barbecue sauce in the formed pan about 1/2 inch deep.
Place chicken breasts (salted) in the pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Put on preheated barbecue grill for 20 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well with a fork.
Do not beat!
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased tube pan or greased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: deep skillet beef stroganoff
directions: Slice stew meat 1/4 inch thick or in small strips 1/4 inch wide.
Brown quickly on medium-high heat in 1/4 cup oleo in skillet.
Push meat to one side.
Add mushrooms and chopped onion. Cook on medium heat until tender.
Add 1 teaspoon seasoning. Blend in meat.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Blend in the remaining ingredients. Can be put in Tupperware and frozen until ready for use.

title: brown turkey gravy
directions: Deglaze pan by stirring 1/4 cup (50 ml.) water into pan with drippings.
Heat, stirring and scraping pan, 2 to 3 minutes. Strain pan juices into 4 cup (1 L) measure.
Remove excess fat, reserving 3 tablespoons (15 ml.) fat.
Add enough chicken broth or water to equal 3 cups (750 ml.) liquid.

title: mama's white mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in juice of lemon and egg whites with mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss-sausage casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sausage and mustard and spread on top.
Arrange cheese on top. Combine, beat and pour over sausage and cheese the remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Allow to come to room temperature and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix mushroom soup and chicken soup with the water. Set aside. Pour rice into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Add about 1/4 of soup mixture. Add chicken and mushrooms. Pour rest of soup mixture over top. Sprinkle with onion soup (optional). Add salt and pepper only if you do not use onion soup mix. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Bring oleo, sugar, syrup and water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook to hard crack stage.
Spread nuts on greased cookie sheet and pour mixture over them.
Sprinkle top of butter mixture with chocolate chips and let melt enough to cover mixture with chocolate.
Let cool and crack with back of knife.

title: yule cake
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and line with waxed paper and then grease the waxed paper.
Place nuts and fruits in large bowl. Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Then sift over the fruit mixture and mix well.
Beat eggs in bowl until light, add vanilla.
Blend with fruit mixture.
Spoon in loaf pan.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.
After baking cool 10 minutes.
Take from pan and cool.
Brush with apple cider.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound breasts between waxed paper to make thinner.
Dip each breast in flour, eggs and bread crumbs. Brown in oil about 5 minutes on each side.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce to cover bottom of shallow baking dish.
Place chicken in dish; cover with sauce and top with cheese (amounts may vary to taste).
Bake until cheese melts and bubbles (about 30 minutes). Serve with fresh salad.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well; add oil, then vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Then stir in apples and pecans.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroon salad
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, coconut and oats together.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Spread mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Put in freezer.
After about 1/2 hour, pop out on foil. Cover with foil and roll a rolling pin over to crush up.

title: creamed chicken
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken stock and cream; stir slowly but steadily until sauce boils; boil a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper; stir some hot sauce into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Blend well; combine rest of sauce.
Add chicken and pimento (if desired).
Season to taste; cover.
Heat over hot water.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and banana. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Pour into greased pans. Bake one hour at 350 degrees. Also makes great muffins. Place in muffin cups and bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Peel eggplant and chop with zucchini and yellow squash.
Cook in a 5-quart pot, using 1 inch of salted water (5 to 8 minutes, until just tender).
Drain in colander.
Put oil in pot and return eggplant, squash and all other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve as a side dish or over rice.
Can add Parmesan as garnish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: paintbrush cookies
directions: Slice roll in 1/4-inch slices, then place on baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Mix egg yolk and water, then divide mix into 4 small dishes.
Mix a drop of food coloring in each dish.
Paint designs on cookies with a small clean paintbrush.
Bake painted cookies in a 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and salt, and sift together three times.
Cream butter thoroughly, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put layers together and cover top and sides with soft chocolate frosting.
Sprinkle sides with nuts.

title: yummy sandwich filling
directions: Blend well.
Refrigerate well until firm and of spreading consistency.

title: da kat's barbecue sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic and onions.
Brown until soft. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Taste for seasoning.
This is a sweet type barbecue sauce.
To make it more pungent, eliminate the beer and increase vinegar to 1 cup.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and add to casserole dish. Combine last 4 ingredients and spread on top of other mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken and vegetables in small baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices and bake for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Pat evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add strawberries.
Fold cream cheese and sugar into Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Top with Jell-O mixture.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cut apricots into pieces in small bowl; pour hot water over all.
Let soften for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve 1/4 cup apricot water; set aside apricot pieces.
Combine butter, sugar and egg in mixing bowl; cream well.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with apricot water and orange juice.
Stir in apricots and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5-inch size) or 2 half pans (3 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes for large pan or 50 minutes for small pans. Refrigerate when cool.

title: apple rice pudding
directions: Bring water to a boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in rice and margarine; cover.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in Marshmallow Creme.
Add all remaining ingredients except eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes. Serve warm or chilled.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Let crumbs stand in milk for 10 minutes, then mix with chicken.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, seasonings, butter and parsley.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake in buttered pan for 25 minutes in a moderate oven.
Garnish with creamed mushrooms, peas or parsley.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli and chicken dish
directions: Boil chicken, cool and take off bone.
Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Butter the dish.
Cut broccoli in pieces and lay out in dish.
Cut chicken in pieces and lay on top of broccoli. Mix the 2 soups and mayonnaise in bowl; pour over chicken.
Layer cheese on top of soups.
Melt butter and pour over croutons. Place croutons on top of cheese.
Place in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Grease 3-quart casserole dish with butter. Mix together onion, eggs, mayonnaise and soup.
Fold in broccoli and place in dish.
Top with 1/2 bag of stuffing.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over everything.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Remove skin from onion, cucumber, tomato and bell pepper; remove seeds from green pepper, tomato and cucumber. Chop vegetables very fine (preferably in food chopper). Soften gelatin in 2 tablespoons water. Mix some mayonnaise to blend.
Add remaining mayonnaise to gelatin mixture and combine this with chopped vegetables which have been well drained. Store in jar in refrigerator to season.

title: dutch butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dampen cloth and put over small drinking glass.
Dip in white sugar and use to flatten cookie balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: hot sausage rolls(polish hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Measure flour.
Cut margarine in small pieces in flour.
Stir in cottage cheese until a soft dough.
Add ice water (2 to 3 teaspoons), if needed.
Divide in 6 parts.
Roll each into 3 x 6-inch.
Spread with 1 teaspoon mustard.
Top with a sausage.
Roll around sausage and encase completely.
Brush with water.
Place, seam edges down, on cookie sheet.
Prick with fork to allow steam to escape.
Mix egg and milk; brush on sausage.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until brown.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: aunt mable's yeast rolls(serves 36)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add 1 cup of boiling water.
Cool.
When lukewarm, add beaten eggs and yeast dissolved in 1 cup cold water.
Add flour, then add salt.
Mix well.
Put into a greased bowl in refrigerator to rise.
Cover.
Let dough chill thoroughly, overnight if possible.
Make rolls into desired shape and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Brush with margarine.
Let rise at least 2 hours or until rolls double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add Karo and sugar to beaten eggs and beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange design of pecan halves on top if desired.
Bake in 350° oven until it begins to brown.
Turn oven to 300° and finish baking until filling is set, about 45 minutes.
(If it browns too fast, it will be too hard on top.)

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add frozen orange juice pineapple and orange slices.	Place in an 8-inch casserole dish allow to gel. Prepare pudding using one cup milk, fold in whip topping and spread over congealed salad.
Top with nuts.
Serves 10.

title: quick cabbage
directions: Wash and shred the cabbage and place it in cold water until ready to use. Put the side meat in a pot with the oil and cook slowly until crispy. Drain the cabbage and add it to the pot along with the 1/4 c. water. Cook on low for 15 minutes, stirring to cook evenly. Add salt to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook broken up sausage in skillet until done; drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well with hands.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° until browned, approximately 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix until smooth.
Chill and roll to 1/4 inch on slightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or just teaspoon onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add peanut butter and milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust and put in freezer.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins or prepare paper liners.
Beat sugar and oil in medium bowl.
Blend in eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in another bowl. Gradually stir dry ingredients into oil mixture, blend well.
Fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
