Spoon batter into tin to 2/3 full. Bake until tester inserted in center of muffins comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper; drain off fat.
Cook noodles; drain.
Put in casserole dish with the rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Heat oil in
skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat.

In small bowl mix onions, pepper, ginger, garlic, curry powder and cumin. Add 2 Tbsp. water and mix into a paste. Add paste to oil and fry for about 2-3 minutes over medium-low heat, stirring constantly.
Add chicken pieces and salt to mixture and stir until well mixed.

title: barbecued burgers
directions: Put beef, pepper, onion, egg and bread crumbs in bowl and mix. Shape into four 1/4 pound patties. Season each with garlic powder and onion salt to taste.
Brush each burger with olive oil to prevent burning.
Grill patties, basting with barbecue sauce. Flip and baste with more sauce.
Serve with platter of sliced red onions and tomatoes, with or without buns.
Good with corn on the cob and potato salad.

title: corned beef with apricot glaze
directions: Place corned beef in Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add pickling spices.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Turn off heat and cool beef at room temperature for 1 hour.
Place beef in a shallow baking pan.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream
Crisco,
butter
and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, then
add vanilla, salt, baking powder, flour and diced orange slices.
Drop
cookie
dough by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake
at
350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: twice baked chicken
directions: Salt and flour chicken.
Fry fast in hot oil just to brown on both sides.
Place in casserole dish.
Put thin slices of onion and 1 strip of bacon on each piece of chicken.
Add enough water to almost cover the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Pour off water and save to make gravy.
Put chicken back in oven just long enough to dry out a little.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring to boil peaches, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Thicken as needed with cornstarch.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, soda and milk.
Pour into butter.
Add fruit mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix well and add 1 cup strawberries.
Cook until center springs back.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cold pack cheese food and cream cheese out to soften.
Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: hibiscus
directions: A good Riesling, Soave, Rose or Chablis would go with any of the recipes in this section.

title: chicken (or turkey) divan
directions: Layer as follows:
meat, broccoli, then cheese.
Mix together next four ingredients.
Pour over meat, broccoli and cheese. Cover with small package of bread stuffing mix.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruited ice cream dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until cream melts.
Add 2/3 cup drained fruit.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with cup of diced fruit.
Serves 6.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald the milk.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir the milk gradually into the egg mixture.
Strain into the pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 325° and bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Combine margarine, onion, poppy seed and mustard in small bowl; set aside.
Slice each roll in middle; spread proceeding mixture on each side of roll.
Place ham and cheese between bread. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Do not drain.
Blend milk, cheese and flour in blender on grind.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add half and half.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil. Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased and floured 12 x 18 x 1-inch cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in pan and bake until middle is done.

title: giant chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts. Spread dough evenly in greased 13-inch round pizza pan.

title: all-in-one cake
directions: Add dates and soda to boiling water; cool.
Mix together the sugar, shortening, eggs, flour and soda.
Add cooled date mixture to sugar, shortening, eggs, flour and soda.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts, chocolate chips and brown sugar. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Beat egg and then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and spread in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare rice. Set aside.
Cut peppers lengthwise into halves. Clean out seeds and pulp.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes. Cook hamburger and onion until slightly brown.
Drain off oil. Add rice and half can tomato soup.
Mix well.
Pack mixture firmly into pepper halves.
Place in foil lined baking pan.
Bring to a boil 1/3 cup vinegar, 1/2 can soup and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Pour over peppers.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef tenderloin with madeira and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Make a 2-inch deep incision the length of the roast so that meat opens and lies flat.
Salt and pepper the inside and spread with Dijon mustard.
Saute mushrooms in pan where bacon was cooked.
Add garlic and shallots and cook for 1 minute. Combine with bacon and spread the mixture down the middle of the roast.
Roll tenderloin to its original shape and tie with butcher's twine.
Heat oil in a large pan and sear roast on all sides until browned.
Place roast in 450° oven and reduce temperature to 375°.
Roast 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow it to sit for 5 minutes.

title: one pan chocolate peanut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg with a fork in an ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Stir in baking mix until moistened.
Press mixture evenly in pan. Bake until light brown, 16 to 18 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Let stand until chocolate chips are softened, 3 to 4 minutes; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Cut into bars about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes about 32 bars.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Stir in gelatin mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, oranges, pineapple, soda and pecans.
Chill until mounds.
Fold in 3/4 of Cool Whip.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut in squares.
Serve with reserved topping.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Wash and dry breasts.
Skin and brown in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic; saute for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Combine flour, salt, pepper and thyme; stir into mixture. Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Crumble in bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add wine.
Reduce heat.
Pour over chicken in roaster and bake at 400° for 3 hours.
Serves 24.

title: cinnamon biscuit loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine all ingredients and set aside.
Separate the biscuit dough into 20 biscuits.
Flatten slightly.
Spoon about 1/4 teaspoon of pecan mixture in the center of each biscuit.
Fold biscuits in half.
Pinch edges to seal. Place biscuits, fold side down, in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan forming 4 rows of 5 biscuits each.
Spoon remaining pecan mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate, pecan side up.
In small bowl combine 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 3 to 4 teaspoons milk.
Drizzle over warm loaf.
Serve in slices or pull apart.

title: punch - slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Combine cold water, pineapple juice, sugar and Jell-O. Place in 5-quart pails. Cover and freeze for at least 48 hours.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Reserve some crumbs to top with.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine.
Line bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan with mixture.
Blend cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat Dream Whip with milk.
Fold this into cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over crumb base.
Top with pie filling.
Add remaining cream cheese mixture. Top with reserved crumbs.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Stir in shrimp and shape into a ball. Cover with seafood cocktail sauce. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: grilled herbed salmon
directions: Press pepper onto both sides of salmon with onion and lemon slices.
Set aside.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Arrange fresh thyme on grill rack. Place salmon on fresh thyme.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until flakes easily when tested with fork.
Transfer to a serving platter, discarding thyme and lemon slices.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal,
flour, salt and baking powder.
Add hot water until
a
smooth
mixture.
Spoon
out into a frypan that oil has been
heated
in.
Brown
on
one
side, then the other. Total cooking time approximately 10 to 15 minutes over a medium fire.

title: pineapple orange molded salad
directions: Melt jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat with beater until smooth.
Add pineapple and orange juice.
Mold until firm.
Serves 6.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix marinade from next three ingredients and add to cucumbers and onions and then add enough water to cover.
Make ahead and refrigerate for several hours.
Lift out of marinade to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, mix sugar and butter until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
In bowl combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients, a little at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Drop by teaspoons several inches apart on a cookie sheet.
For flat cookies, press with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar before baking.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: summertime stew
directions: Note:
Add tomato sauce or small amount of water, as desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, combine with soup and pepper.
Add onions.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Garnish with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Mix together and put into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garlic cheese pat
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: israeli vegetable stew
directions: Put olive oil in large, covered saucepan.
Cook eggplant and onions for about 25 minutes, until slightly browned.
Add garlic and green pepper; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar and basil; simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Add parsley, olives and pimento; simmer gently for a further 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste (take account of the salty olives and adjust seasonings accordingly).
Can be made a day in advance and reheated.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
Take ground beef.
Crumble the end piece of bread into ground beef.
Add egg.
Add several shakes of onion flakes, if desired.
Use 3 to 4 squeezes of ketchup or until enough.
Add milk.
Mix together with hands or stir well with spoon.
Put in glass dish and put in oven.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Drain grease from dish and top meat loaf with ketchup.

title: grandma martha's ham pot pie
directions: Place potatoes (sliced) in roaster; sprinkle with parsley. Cut pieces of cooked ham and dough into squares.
Alternate layers and finally cover with ham broth.
Bake slowly at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Divide and shape into 2 or 3 rolls and chill.
Slice and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls flat into a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and spices. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with finely chopped raw vegetables. Slice and refrigerate until served.

title: oven omelet
directions: Mix. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, flavoring, eggs, cream or half and half in blender or mixer on high speed until well blended.
Pour into container and finish filling with milk to the fill line.

title: make ahead lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add spaghetti mix, tomato paste and water. Simmer 10 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups sauce; arrange layer of uncooked lasagna noodles. Top with some sauce and some of each cheese in layers. Repeat, making sure noodles are immersed in sauce. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Let stand 15 minutes. Cut into squares to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: glazed lemon carrots
directions: Simmer carrots in enough salted water to cover until tender. Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Saute for 10 minutes, shaking the pan so each piece of carrot will be coated with the dressing.

title: mexicali meat pie
directions: Beat egg slightly in mixing bowl.
Add ground beef, corn, cracker crumbs, chili sauce, sweet peppers, onion and oregano. Mix well.
Press meat mixture firmly into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread topping (recipe follows) on filling.
Top with olives and bacon.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: betsy's muffins
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add buttermilk and shortening (or oil) and beat.
Mix all dry ingredients (except bran flakes) and beat.
Add bran flakes and stir by hand.
Let stand in covered bowl in refrigerator for 2 days.
Spoon mixture into muffin tins and bake at 400 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Can keep mix in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: puppy chow candy
directions: Melt together; first place in large bowl the 9 cups of Rice Chex.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Place 2 cups of powdered sugar in paper bag; shake and place Rice Chex mixture inside. Shake up.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: gherkin salat
directions: Slice cucumbers as thin as possible by hand or in food processor.
Slice onions.
Tear up parsley.
Sprinkle salt over all and stir well.
Add 3 or 4 ice cubes.
Cover and let set for several hours.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Drain very well.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Gradually add milk to soup, stirring over low heat to make a smooth sauce.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, onions and pepper. Arrange 1/2 noodles, ham and sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine the 2 cups of flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbs are the size of small peas.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: icebox cake
directions: Line Pyrex dish with wax paper.
Mix well all ingredients by hand; put into Pyrex dish.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: recital cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar, water and vanilla. Sift flour and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts. Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: coconut sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and Crisco all together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in sour cream, coconut and flavorings.
Add milk.
Add flour and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cocoa waggy cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in pan Mix last 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add to first mixture in pan, stir.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: exalee's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Add crushed vanilla wafers, milk and pecans.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: cajun toasted almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix spices in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, combine egg white and water.
Beat with
a fork until frothy.
Add the almonds and stir to coat well.
Sprinkle the spices over the nuts, again stirring to coat.
Place on a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and roast 45 minutes, stirring each 15 minutes or so.
Let cool before storing airtight.

title: sweet potato souffle crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with crunch topping.
Dribble melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana cranberry bread
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water in pan; cook 5 minutes and add cranberries.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Cool and drain.
Cream shortening with remaining sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; add walnuts.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, beating well.
Fold in 1 cup cranberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour pie filling into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan or 9-inch pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle on pie filling.
Bake until topping is light brown, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Place onions and peppers on chops.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken picante
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Cover the chicken with one-half of the grated cheese.
Pour the entire jar of picante sauce over the chicken, completely covering it.
Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Place remaining cheese on top of dish and continue baking for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat.
Stir in other ingredients until batter is smooth.
Pour 1/2 cup for each waffle.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat in saucepan until dissolved the Jell-O mix, sugar and pineapple.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix thoroughly and pour in dish and refrigerate.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: First Layer:
Crushed cookies and melted margarine
stirred and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole, then top with the crackers, mixed with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lumpy's
directions: Mix all together and season with garlic powder, salt, a few drops of lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs and pour into sugar mixture.
Add syrup, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Stir and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain; add butter and cheese. Replace lid until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve.
May use with cauliflower.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter and stem apples; cook in cider until tender; put through food mill.
Cook sauce down until it stands up on a teaspoon.
Add spices and sugar and cook at least an hour more. Put in jars and process 10 minutes (I use pint jars).
Also, I do this in the late fall after we have a fire in the wood burner so it can cook down on the wood burner.

title: scampi sauce
directions: Fry bacon.
Chop into small pieces.
Put into small pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Saute but don't brown.
Great for dipping shrimp, crab strips or clams.
Can be put over fish in foil (bake at 375° for 35 minutes).

title: apricot bread
directions: Pour boiling water over apricots; let stand until tender. Drain water and save.
(If you don't have a cup, add water.) Roughly chop apricots.
Pour liquid into mixing bowl.
Add baking soda, sugar and eggs; mix well with wooden spoon.
Add apricots, flour, baking powder and nuts; mix well again.
Butter and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf tins.
Divide batter into tins; bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, until straw comes out clean. Cool on racks and serve.

title: sausage-potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In roasting pan, combine potatoes, cabbage, oil, salt, thyme, paprika and pepper.
Bake until potatoes are almost tender, about 30 minutes.
Add kielbasa.
Bake until heated through and potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in a saucepan over high heat bring broth, red onion, parsley, vinegar and mustard to a boil.
Remove from heat; pour over potato mixture and toss to coat.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple quick pie
directions: Mix together and pour in a graham cracker crust.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine flour and salt. Stir and set aside.
Combine orange slices, dates, pecans and coconut.

Stir in 1/2 cup of the flour mixture. Set aside. Cream the butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine buttermilk and soda, mixing well. Add flour mixture, alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Add candy mixture; stir until well blended.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 pans well.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: depression jam
directions: If you're the do-it-yourself type, here are some recipes for making yogurt at home.

You might not have the pleasure of milking your own cow, goat or camel like the biblical people did, but you can still turn out some healthful, tasty yogurt and maybe add a few years to your life at the same time.

title: cheddar whipped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, bring potatoes and water to a boil. Continue cooking until the potatoes are very tender. Drain well. Return to saucepan over low heat, stirring until potatoes are dry. Transfer to a large bowl.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, heat milk and margarine until steaming and margarine is melted. Add to potatoes in bowl along with cheese, salt and pepper.
Using mixer, beat potatoes until blended and creamy smooth. Garnish with chives.

title: fruit salad
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, 1 layer crushed pineapple, 1 layer sliced bananas and 1 layer miniature marshmallows.
Prepare jello according to directions.
Let set to syrupy stage.
Pour over fruit and let set.

title: cajun shrimp casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter; saute celery, pepper and onions for 7 minutes stirring constantly.
Add flour, salt, mace, curry powder, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce, stirring until well blended.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add shrimp; cook about 3 minutes.
Pour into a buttered 6 x 10-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: cranberry mold salad
directions: Mix the package jello with the boiling water.
Add all the other ingredients and chill.

title: vegetable or potato chip dip
directions: Stir all
ingredients together until well blended.
Add green onions, dill weed and the Beau Monde seasoning.
Refrigerate. Recipe may be cut in half.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Cook sugar, water and butter to firm ball stage.
Pour over the egg whites, beating constantly.

title: easy one dish dinner
directions: In big frying pan, brown about 1 pound ground beef.
Put noodles on top. Beat together sour cream, tomato juice, water, minced onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce. Pour mixture over noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in 1 tablespoon per cup of boiling water.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1 square unsweetened chocolate in a saucepan.
Blend in sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, egg, crumbs and coconut in butter/chocolate mixture.
Mix well and press into ungreased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate.
Mix 1/4 cup butter, milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Chill.
Melt 2 squares of unsweetened chocolate and spread evenly over chilled filling.
Chill again.
Cut into squares before completely firm.

title: apple relish
directions: Peel apples and oranges and grind them; also raisins.
Add all other ingredients to this and cook for 35 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: canned green tomatoes for frying
directions: Cut ham in chunks approximately 1 x 1-inch. Put into quart jars. (Do not add water.) Add 1 teaspoon canning salt per quart. Cook in pressure cooker at 15 pounds pressure for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer for as long as mix directs.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan which has been greased and floured at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight layered green salad
directions: Shred the lettuce and place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch serving glass dish. Top lettuce with green onions, then celery and water chestnuts. Open the package of frozen peas and break apart. Sprinkle frozen peas evenly over salad.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over the top. Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder. Cover and chill in refrigerator for as long as 24 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions in bowl; add salt.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix dates and fruit with 5 tablespoons flour.
Blend with rest of the ingredients and press into 2 greased and waxed lined loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze. Can be used as a dessert.

title: honey crunch snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
In a saucepan put butter, honey and brown sugar.
Heat until melted and mixed.
Pour over cereal and mix until cooled.
Spread on cookie sheet; bake 15 minutes at 300° and then at 325° for another 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
When mix is golden brown, spread on waxed paper and sprinkle with raisins.
Cool completely and store in tight container.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put all ingredients.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).
Serve with a nice green salad and rolls.

title: tequila salad
directions: Shake reserved pineapple syrup, 1/4 cup lime juice, the sugar, tequila, oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt in tightly covered container. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut avocados lengthwise in half; remove pits.
Peel avocados; cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Sprinkle pieces with lime juice.
Cut pineapple slices in half.
Pare and section grapefruit and oranges; cut sections in half, if desired. Just before serving, toss avocado and fruit; place on salad greens. Sprinkle with walnuts and salt.
Serve with dressing.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lazy woman chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients or mix in sheet pan.
Make 3 holes in flour mix.
In one, place oil; in one, put vinegar.
In last hole, put vanilla.
Pour water over mixture.
Mix well with fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, alternately with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Add baking powder to milk, then add to mixture.
Stir in nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in 2 round pans at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cake comes out of the oven, prick the top and pour juice from the pineapple over the cake.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes, then mix with eggs and salt and pepper.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° to 375° for about an hour.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Stir in sherbet until dissolved, then add drained mandarin oranges and the pineapple. Pour into quart and a half mold.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix ground chuck, egg, some onion, salt, and pepper to taste. Use enough cracker crumbs to hold it together.
Make into a loaf and center in casserole.
Mix vegetables and put around meat loaf. Chop onion and potato and put over mixed vegetables.
Over this, pour the can of tomatoes with more salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: italian style green beans
directions: Remove casing from Italian sausage; crumble and saut in olive oil until all pink has disappeared.
Place frozen green beans, can of crushed tomatoes and sauteed sausage in a 13 x 11 deep baking pan or casserole.
Toss all ingredients until mixed. Top with cheese.
Bake in a 300° oven for 35 minutes.
Recipe can be multiplied several times.
Great for large parties and gatherings.

title: pecan turtle cookies
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Blend well. Pat firmly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly.
Cook 2/3 butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar in saucepan until mixture boils.
Pour caramel over crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Leave 5 minutes or until melted.
Spread evenly while warm.
Cool and cut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add pineapple.
Add sugar to cranberries and let stand for a few minutes.
Add all ingredients to jello and refrigerate until firm, overnight is better.

title: vege chicken ala can can
directions: Use soup can to measure water. Brown rice may be used instead of Minute rice.
Add liquid from chicken and cook about 1 1/4 hours.
Dump all together, mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with canned onion rings at end of baking.

title: country potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes no more than 3 minutes with peels on.
Cool. Peel skins off and grate.
Add next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, preheat oven to 325° and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Uncover and spread cornflakes and melted butter on top; bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: southern barbecue sauce
directions: Put vinegar, butter and lemon juice in saucepan on stove; heat to boiling.
Then add peppers and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
May be used on cooked pork shoulder roast.

title: 10 cup cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter, butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, soda and baking powder and stir.
Then add to this mixture the oats, nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, coconut and flour.
Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: braised celery wedges
directions: Trim stem ends of celery; cut stalk crosswise about 6 inches from base (reserving leaves for soups, stews, etc.).
Cut lengthwise into 4 to 6 wedges and arrange in large skillet. Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; add to skillet along with oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 8 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender.
Remove celery to heated platter; scatter pimento over celery and serve.
Lovely with broiled lemon flavored chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Mix water, jello and marshmallows in pan over medium heat until marshmallows have melted.
Let cool completely.
Stir rest of ingredients into cooled jello mixture.
Put into serving bowl and chill.

title: make ahead punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients and freeze.
Twenty-four hours before needed, place in refrigerator and let it thaw until slushy. To serve pour into punch bowl with Sprite.

title: black beans and pasta(low-fat)
directions: Over medium heat, warm oil; saute pepper, onion, oregano, garlic and cumin until vegetables are tender. Add tomato sauce, beans and hot pepper sauce; bring to boil. Reduce heat to low. Cook about 10 minutes. Toss with hot macaroni. Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: garden casserole
directions: Layer the potatoes and onion in a casserole dish.
Cover with the mixed vegetables.
Add the mushroom soup and cover with corn. Spread with tomato sauce. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove cover and brown slightly.

title: furr's pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Note:
an equivalent amount of egg substitute may be used for the eggs which are uncooked in this recipe.

title: the simolon's favorite cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and egg; beat well.
Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: maw-maw's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: express goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes and uncooked macaroni, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes (or until card game is over).

title: chili
directions: Brown onions and hamburger in an electric skillet. Add spices and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Then let simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Using the electric skillet is the key to the best chili ever.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix with spoon and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: meat sauce
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat corn oil over medium heat. Add next 4 ingredients.
Cook, stirring, 10 minutes or until beef is browned.
In blender container, place tomatoes.
Cover.
Blend on high speed 30 seconds or until chopped.
Add to beef mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes.
Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour 1 cup sugar over mixture and toss often over and over.
Heat remaining ingredients to boil; pour liquids over the mixture.
Let stand for 3 hours or overnight.
This will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: easy mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; strain and rinse.
Leave in pan.
Now add butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Keep on low until bubbly.
Now put some macaroni in a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex bowl, then some cheese. Repeat until all elbows and cheese are gone.
Mix together.
Now put 3 slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Cook in double boiler the egg yolks, milk, butter and vanilla. Mix flour and brown sugar. Add to the milk. Cook until thick. Let cool and pour into baked pie shells. Cover with meringue. Makes 2 pies.

title: danish puff
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine 1 cube margarine and 1 cup flour.
Mix like pie crust with small amount of water.
Pat into a 12 x 3-inch strip.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1/4 cup warm water; stir.
Add sugar, stirring to dissolve yeast completely.
Add salt, milk mixture and cooking oil.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead with spoon about 20 to 25 times.
Cover and let stand and rise for 2 hours.
Punch and knead with greased hands about 10 to 12 times.
Make rolls and put on greased baking pan.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Yields 15 rolls.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Add (top off) with 7-Up when serving.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in boiling water.
Cook until clear, stirring often.
Add jello and cool.
Pour over fresh berries in a 10-inch baked pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet munchies
directions: Cook margarine, white sugar, corn syrup and vanilla until soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Pour over Chex mixture and mix well. Put on cookie sheet to cool.
Stir while mixture is cooling.
Put in freezer bag.
Break up before serving.
They will stick together in humid weather.
Store in refrigerator.
(Nita LeBlanc.)

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake 1/2 of mix in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, margarine and milk.
Pour over baked portion of cake.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake mix on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 275°, then 10 minutes at 350°.
Needs no frosting!

title: low-fat trout amandine
directions: Combine margarine, chopped onion and 1 tablespoon lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until margarine melts and onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in toasted almond slices and chopped fresh parsley.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and then add the remaining ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Alternately mix dry ingredients with zucchini and other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: crock-pot down south barbecue
directions: Put half of onions in bottom of crock-pot, then add meat and other ingredients (except barbecue sauce and large onion) with remaining onion on top.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving. Makes a great vegetable dip.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together melted margarine and peanut butter. Mix graham crackers and powdered sugar; add to peanut butter mixture. Press on to cookie sheet using wax paper on top and rolling with rolling pin. Melt chocolate chips and spread over top of peanut butter mixture. Let cool; cut and enjoy! Tastes like Reese's cups.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In a medium saucepan,
combine
sugar,
milk, margarine and eggs.
Cook over medium heat
until
mixture
starts
to bubble, stirring constantly.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients. Cool until frosting will spread consistently.
Will frost a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake or a 3 layer cake.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop.
Run through colander.
Bring juice and 2 cups sugar to a rolling boil for 3 to 4 minutes (don't over boil), or use juice with Sure-Jell recipe.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: cinnamon orange chicken
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Lightly coat chicken pieces in mixture; shake off excess.
Heat butter and olive oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
When hot, add chicken pieces and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken from the pan.
Add chopped onion; cook until onion is tender.
Return chicken to pan. Add orange juice and raisins.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan; keep warm. Increase heat to high; boil remaining juices rapidly, stirring occasionally until sauce reduces and thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Place hot cooked rice on a serving platter.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Top with orange sauce; garnish with parsley and orange slices.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt together.
Add syrup, water, butter and eggs; mix well.
Cook 10 minutes or more, until thickened, stirring continuously.
Cool about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat about 5 minutes and spread over any layer cake.
Covers about 4 layers.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour and eggs.
Add pineapple, milk and sweet potatoes.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and set.

title: red cucumber pickles
directions: Soak prepared cucumbers in 2 1/2 gallons of water and 2 cups lime for 24 hours.
Rinse several times.
Soak in tap water for 3 hours.
Combine food coloring, 1 cup vinegar, alum and cucumbers with enough water to cover them.
Simmer for 3 hours, drain. Combine the 3 cups vinegar, 3 cups water, red hots, cinnamon and sugar, bring almost to boil.
Pour over the pickles on Monday, let stand 24 hours.
Tuesday reheat and let stand 24 hours.
Repeat Wednesday and Thursday.
Seal on Friday.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted or until 290° is reached on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda until syrup becomes foamy.
Pour over 4 quarts popped popcorn.
Stir until corn is well coated.
Butter hands and press corn into balls.

title: fantastic brownies
directions: Melt chocolates and 3 sticks margarine.
Cool.
Beat 6 eggs with 2 cups sugar until light in color.
Add chocolate.
Stir in dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 12 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut off the crust of bread.
Butter bread on both sides and cut each into 4 quarters.
Place layer of bread on bottom of oiled casserole.
Layer cheese and bread alternately in casserole.
Mix well the milk, beaten eggs and salt.
Pour liquid mixture into the casserole over the bread.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Serves 4 as a main dish, 6 as a side dish.

title: chocolate chip candy
directions: In large bowl, combine chocolate chips, butter and vanilla. Combine in saucepan sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat exactly 6 minutes after boil starts.
Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Stir until butter and chips melt and mixture starts to thicken.
Pour mixture into lightly greased pan. Let stand 5 to 6 hours.
Cut into squares.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green peppers.
Drain off grease. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then let simmer 2 hours.

title: turkey chili with rice
directions: In skillet pan, simmer turkey, onions and green pepper until tender.
Drain off fat.
Prepare rice according to directions and set aside.
Chop tomatoes and add to meat along with their liquid. Add chili powder and tomato sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Drain liquid from kidney beans.
Add beans and rice.
Simmer until hot. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with French bread and tossed salad.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fettuccine supreme
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup softened butter on low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add parsley, basil and pepper; mix well.
Add boiling water; beat until mixture is smooth.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain well.
Saute garlic in 1/4 cup melted butter in a small skillet until tender. Combine garlic mixture and warm noodles, tossing gently.
Add cream cheese mixture and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; toss gently. Place in serving dish; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add instant pudding. Beat with wire whisk until blended well 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the rocks into pudding mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Garnish with gum drop flowers.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine rice, beef broth, beef consomme, onion and mushrooms in a casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour into casserole dish. Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable and bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours. Cut a cavity out of a loaf of Vienna bread.
Cut the removed bread into cubes.
Put dip into cavity.
Dip bread cubes into the dip, as well as carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and any other veggies you like!

title: pork with garlic mustard sauce
directions: Mince garlic.
Slice shallot.
Cut pork in pieces.
Dredge tenderloin in salt, pepper and flour.
Saute until brown; put aside and keep pork warm.
Cook shallot and garlic in pan over medium heat.
Add chicken broth; scrape up drippings.
Stir in mustard and parsley; cook until it thickens.

title: selma's virginia pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and continue to cream about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, by folding them in. Add cake flour, a little at a time.
Slowly add milk, then flavorings.
Add baking powder last.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in freezer container. Put in mixer bucket.
Alternate ice and rock salt around as mixer works.
When crank won't turn, ice cream should be done.

title: baked mackerel
directions: Wash and pat dry with paper towel.
Place skin side down in a shallow pan lined with foil (for easy cleaning).
Sprinkle fish lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with a bit of butter. Add milk to nearly cover the fish and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: kris' nacho chip dip
directions: In skillet, brown meat, onion and one green pepper.
Cut up tomatoes and put in large bowl with soup and beans (do not drain beans).
Mix in soup-bean mix.
After thoroughly mixed, put in casserole and cook at 250° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with taco cheese and other green pepper, cut in strips. Put back in oven and cook another 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: chicken broccoli pie
directions: Makes two pies.
Cook and cube chicken breasts.
Microwave frozen broccoli for 6 minutes.
Put bottom crust in pie plates. Layer chicken, broccoli, and cheese.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add milk and Bisquick.
Stir but leave mixture lumpy.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over each pie.
Add top crust.
Bake 45 - 50 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into cubes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and add poppy seed and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chow mein
directions: Fry hamburger or chow mein meat.
Combine with beef bouillon, celery, onion, salt, soy sauce and water; cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add cornstarch, dissolved in 1/2 cup water to thicken. Then add drained bean sprouts, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots. Add Kitchen Bouquet for color.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.

title: mainstay french toast
directions: Cook sugar, butter and syrup until thick.
Pour into oven baking dish or pan.
Spread apples on top.
Whisk remaining ingredients and pour over bread slices which have been placed on top of apples.
Cover and refrigerate overnight Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: sesame seed salad dressing
directions: Shake vigorously in jar or whip in blender.

title: shake-it-up chicken nuggets
directions: Crush crumbs by placing in Ziploc bag and rolling a rolling pin over bag.
Open bag and add Parmesan cheese.
Re-seal bag and shake to mix.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently
Then boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Stir in soda and cream of tartar.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Turn into shallow pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven, pour onto brown paper (I use grocery sack split open).
Cool completely, break apart and store in covered (tightly) container.
(May be doubled for larger amount.)

title: vaughans baked chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in casserole.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with garden salad and rye bread.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add juice of oranges, skin and sour milk.
Sift together baking soda, flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown on bottom. Makes a large batch.
Taste best when iced with orange flavored icing.

title: caramel apple-walnut squares(15 to 20 servings)
directions: Crust:
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of the mixture. Press the remaining mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake the crust layer in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: holly bar
directions: Blend butter, powdered sugar and egg yolks.
Mix in flour. Press and flatten mixture in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix condensed milk, vanilla, lemon juice and chopped cherries.
Set aside.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg, water and vinegar. Mix well.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower, Bac*Os and cheese in a bowl.
Cover with mayo.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Cover and chill overnight.
Toss with salt and pepper before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled eggs and red beets
directions: Boil the ingredients together for 10 minutes.
Boil young beets until tender; skin and cover with the liquid.
Let beets stand in this liquid for several days.
Remove and add whole hard-cooked, shelled eggs to the liquid.
Let pickle for 2 days before using.

title: shrimp or chicken gumbo
directions: Heat heavy 4-quart aluminum or cast-iron pot.
Then add cold oil to hot pan (so food won't stick).
Stir in flour with wooden or metal spoon.
(Do not use plastic or Teflon this gets so hot it will melt them.)
Stir, stir, stir.
Do not leave unattended. Brown to the color of milk chocolate; then add all chopped veggies and stir several minutes.
Then add garlic salt and pepper.
Add water a little at a time to consistency of gravy (not too thin). Add chicken; cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken or shrimp is done.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar, then set aside.
Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crushed cookies, cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture in an 8-inch flower pot.
Decorate with seasonal flower and watch to see if it gets eaten!

title: chili rellenos(makes 12)
directions: Heat the broiler.
Broil the chiles, turning them until the skin is charred on all sides, about 15 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, peel leaving stems intact (can be put in plastic bag to make them easier to peel).

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper and salt in skillet.
Add salted cooked macaroni and tomato sauce or juice.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes over medium heat.

title: lime delight
directions: Chill milk in freezer until icy cold. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Chill until partially set, then whip until fluffy. Stir in sugar and lime juice. Whip evaporated milk until stiff. Fold into gelatin mixture. Mix together wafer crumbs and melted butter. Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Pour gelatin mixture over crust. Chill overnight until firm. Top with shaved chocolate. Cut into squares. (Can also be made in spring mold pan.) Garnish with strawberry for color (optional). Enjoy. Very light dessert.

title: mexican torte
directions: Pour semi-sweet chocolate bits into top of double boiler.
Add 1 cup sour cream and 1 tablespoon of the powdered sugar and heat over simmering water, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Place pan of sauce in cold water to cool; stir occasionally.
Set one of the flour tortillas on a serving plate and spread evenly with a third of the chocolate mixture.
Cover with another tortilla, another third of the sauce, then a third tortilla, the balance of the sauce and the last tortilla.
Make as level as possible.

title: garlic chops and gravy
directions: Brown chops in garlic, margarine and spices.
Then turn the heat down.
Add water, enough to 1/2 way up the side of the chops. Slowly simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: roasted asparagus-raspberry salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Toss asparagus with oil, salt and pepper. Spread over baking sheet. Roast until tender (8 to 10 minutes). Cool asparagus.

title: four layer chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Add butter; mix well.
Spread into a 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Chill.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.
Chop vegetables.
Heat cooking oil in heavy skillet.
Saute vegetables.
Remove vegetables and save.
Dredge pieces of meat in flour.
Brown quickly on each side.
Drain most of fat from pan.
Replace meat; cover with vegetables.
Mix tomato soup with water and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tilt until bottom is covered.
Put other ingredients into pan.
Stir with fork until blended (2 minutes).
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes clean.
Cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar or frosted.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Grate eggs fine, and mix all ingredients.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine in boiling water and drain.
Saute garlic in margarine.
Add fettuccine and toss carefully.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until sauce clings to fettuccine.
Season with pepper.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, then add eggs (one at a time); beat well.
Add flour, beat lemon and vanilla extract.
Add Seven-Up last.
Grease and flour pan, then bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: georgia's beef stroganoff
directions: In hot butter in
skillet;
saute
onions
until golden. Stir in meat, flour, salt, pepper, paprika and mushrooms; saute 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer
uncovered
minutes.
Stir
in sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve on buttered noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Melt butter over medium heat and cook chopped shallots five minutes.
Thoroughly blend in flour, then add both soups.
Cook another five minutes, then add crawfish tails, sherry or wine, pepper and hot sauce.
Taste before adding salt.
Heat thoroughly, then fill pastry shells.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls and press down with fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese chicken with cashews
directions: Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong baking dish and microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 4 minutes.
While the oil is heating, combine all remaining ingredients, except green pepper and cashews.
Add chicken mixture to oil and microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Add green pepper and cashews.
Cover.
Microwave at power level High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until green pepper and chicken are cooked, stirring twice.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Refrigerate dough for easier handling.
Roll chilled dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan pie(microwave)
directions: Place butter in medium size glass bowl.
Cook on power level 7 for 1 1/2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pastry shell.
Pour mixture into shell.
Cook on power level 7 for 10 to 12 minutes or until custard center is set.
Cool and serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Mix remaining ingredients together and stir in .
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 6 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in hot water to thaw; drain and put into bowl. Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Layer cheese on top.
Bake additional time until cheese melts.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in an ovenproof baking dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and black olives or cherry tomatoes, as desired.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 8.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Pop corn and roast pecans.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, honey and syrup; cook 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Pour this mixture over popped corn and roasted pecans.
Mix well until popcorn is covered with mixture.
(Best if stored in metal containers.
It gets a little soggy in plastic containers.)

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil together sugar and vinegar; boil 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Drain and wash sauerkraut; add rest of ingredients. When liquid is cool, pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight. The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: lunchbox cake
directions: Grease and flour the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate pieces and nuts in a large mixing bowl; blend well at the lowest speed of the mixer, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with the chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter in a heavy 10-inch skillet.
Set over medium heat; bring to boil and boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and extract until evenly blended.
Turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan and spread to corners.
Chill before cutting into squares.
Yields about 2 pounds fudge.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Dredge in flour and brown.
Lay in baking dish.
Layer with onions, pepper and mushrooms.
Pour on liquid (water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce).
Cover dish and bake at 275° to 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line in an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Overlap them slightly.
Bake 375° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended and spread over crust. Arrange fruit over cream cheese and layer glaze with combined marmalade and water.
Chill.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Clean broccoli and cut off the flower.
Mix rest of ingredients and shake well.
Pour over broccoli.

title: no-time vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients except pasta in pressure cooker; cook 20 minutes.
Add pasta.
Cook until done.
Additional water may be added with pasta, if thinner soup is desired.

title: famous chocolate dessert
directions: Beat
Dream Whip according to directions; fold in fudge topping.
Line
9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with half graham crackers; cover with half chocolate mixture; add another layer of graham crackers
and
remaining
chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts
over	top.
Cover
and
refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.
Delicious.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer over medium heat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk, then add onions.
Drop by teaspoon into deep hot cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with fish.

title: freezer peanut butter-choc. chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut
butter
and sugar at medium speed of an electric mixer
until
light
and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla, beating
well.
Combine
flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels. Shape dough into
logs;	wrap
in waxed paper and freeze at least 8
hours.
Cut
dough
into
1/4-inch
slices; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake
at	250° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let stand 1 minute; remove cookies to wire racks and cool completely.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
If using food processor; drain.
Cover peppers and onions with boiling water; drain.
Add peppers, onions and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars.

title: our favorite cheese ball
directions: Mix together except for one package of pecans.
Roll pecans on outside before serving.
If you put pecans inside, don't make too far ahead.

title: blueberry upside-down cake
directions: Place 1 tablespoon margarine in round glass dish and microwave on High for 35 seconds.
Combine blueberries, cornstarch and lemon peel in bowl.
Spoon over melted margarine.
Beat 4 tablespoons margarine and sugar; add egg and beat.
Combine flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk to creamed margarine mixture. Add vanilla.
Spread over berries in baking dish.
Microwave 8 minutes on Medium, then on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Rotate 2 to 3 times; test for doneness.
Let stand 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add shortening and work in until crumblike texture.
Pour in buttermilk and work up as a stiff dough.
Pour out on well floured surface.
Work in flour with hands until stickiness is gone.
Roll out with floured dough roller and cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 44 biscuits.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Slice chicken breasts diagonally across grain into about 4 pieces each.
Roll in flour and set aside.
In large skillet, saute garlic quickly in 2 tablespoons butter and remove; set aside.
Saute chicken until just tender; remove and keep warm. Cook spinach in small amount of water.
Remove; keep warm and save cooking water.

title: chili with chicken
directions: In olive oil saute onion and garlic until clear. Remove from heat. In large skillet, fry chicken or turkey until brown, then add to onion and garlic. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: low carb hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients. Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until heated through. Serve with your favorite dippers.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine the cream, chocolate chips, cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Cover and microwave on high for 3-4 minutes or until chips are melted; stir until smooth. Add bread cubes; toss to coat.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
I blot the sausage several times with paper towels to absorb as much grease as possible.
Beat eggs.
Tear bread and mix with milk.
Add to eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake until set and beginning to brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Dissolve soda in sour cream and add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.

title: lithuanian doughnuts(ausukes)
directions: Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Mix baking soda in sour cream. Add all ingredients together.
Knead on a floured board.
Roll out flat.
Cut into 2 x 3-inches long making a slit in center. Twist into bows.
Drop in hot fat and fry until light brown. Drain on paper towel.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: roy byers' nut bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into small or regular size bread pan or baking (deep) dish or bowl.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrot fine.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise; mix well.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers; add salt.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook.
Will change color.
Put in jars and seal.

title: coconut crust pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and melted margarine in bowl.
Add milk, mix well.
Add vanilla and coconut. Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 325° until light brown.
Makes own crust.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes. Cover with water and parboil 5 minutes with salt added.
Heat chicken soup mixed with milk. Add cheese and onion.
Layer drained potatoes and soup mixture in baking dish. Top with a ring of potatoes, a little cheese and a dusting of paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a large saucepan over medium-high heat until the beef is brown, stirring to separate meat; drain fat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix with beater and pour into 9 1/2 x 11 buttered baking dish.

title: glazed honey beets
directions: Wash and cut beet stems to within 2-inches of beet.
Cook about 12 minutes or until tender.
Cool and peel.

title: stained glass fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: baked pear pudding
directions: In buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole, arrange the pears decoratively. In food processor, fitted with steel blade, blend the milk, cream, 2/3 cup sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla until batter just combined.
Pour the batter over the pears.
Sprinkle the top with the remaining 1/3 cup sugar and dot with butter. Bake in upper third of a preheated hot oven at 425° for 50 minutes or until top is golden and pudding is set.
Serve it warm or at room temperature with whipped cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Roll in balls (large).
Roll in sugar.
Press bottom of drinking glass in sugar and use to flatten balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes (time these).

title: s'mores
directions: For each S'mores, spread 1 graham cracker with 1 teaspoon peanut butter.
Then sprinkle with about 10 Log House chocolate chips and 8 miniature marshmallows.
Place under broiler until marshmallows are toasty.
Top with second graham cracker.
Press down firmly.

title: brown rice
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cut up broccoli and onion.
Cook in boiling water about 15 minutes; drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and then simmer.

title: spoon icebox rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water.
Melt oleo and add to yeast; add sugar, egg and flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well (can use mixer).
Put in a large airtight container and refrigerate.
Best made the day before; will keep several days.
Bake at 400° until brown.
This would make about 30 servings of rolls.

title: jo's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in other ingredients. Pour into buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: creamy hash browns
directions: At least 1 hour before baking, put all ingredients in 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and a small amount of paprika.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: jan's lemon pie
directions: Grate fresh lemon rind to make 2 teaspoons, then squeeze and set aside.
Separate eggs, reserve whites for meringue.
Mix together sugar, salt, flour and lemon rind.
Add water.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken.
After slightly beating egg yolks.
Put about 3 tablespoons of hot mixture in and mix.
Add rest of egg yolk mixture and lemon juice to hot mixture and stir until it comes to a boil.
Add butter and cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue (seal all edges around pie).

title: pineapple-cheese christmas casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together pineapple and cheese. Set aside.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Add to the fruit and cheese mixture.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 11-inch or a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Spread crushed crackers over top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook onions and celery slowly in butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix gently.
Bake in greased baking dish or put in greased crock-pot on high for approximately 1/2 hour, then on low at least 3 hours.

title: magic brew
directions: Combine juices, lemonade, cherries and orange slices.
Mix well; chill.
Just before serving, add sherbet and ginger ale. Serve over ice cubes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until pick comes out clean.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over top of cake; cool.

title: salsa cruda(mild tomato sauce for tacos)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.
Makes 3 cups.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Place a sponge cake on a dessert plate.
Top each sponge cake with a generous scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Top with 2 to 3 tablespoons of strawberry sauce.
Serve immediately.
Decorate with almonds if you like.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add crab meat last so lumps don't get broken up.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or bread.
You can make ahead and bake
just before serving.
I usually double recipe as it goes fast.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese, chili and Ro-Tel in medium saucepan, mixing well.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in thirds.
Crumble 1/3 sheet cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1/3 pudding.
Add
1/3 of everything else in order given.
Repeat for second and third layer. Garnish with cherries or anything you wish.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Mix and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove at once. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on brown paper.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Drain and mix ingredients and set aside.

title: ida duff's chili sauce
directions: Chop fine and boil 1 1/2 hours the tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Add the vinegar, sugar, mustard (wet with cold vinegar). Add the salt and spices.
Boil 1 1/2 hours longer or until thickened. Stir occasionally.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: rolled-out dumplings(kentucky-style)
directions: Cut in shortening; add more milk if needed.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Drop on boiling gravy, then cover and turn heat to low. Cook 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add okra, onion, green pepper and celery; saute 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add water, tomatoes, garlic, bay leaf, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp last 10 minutes of cooking.
Serve hot with large spoonful of rice for each serving.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients except walnuts and frosting.
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds. Scrape bowl constantly.
Beat on high 3 minutes, scraping bowl. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: chunky peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat in a heavy saucepan, both sugars, milk, coffee and corn syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugars are dissolved.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, without stirring, until temperature of 238° is reached or a soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Do not mix.
When mixture is lukewarm, beat until thick and creamy.
Quickly pour into greased 7 x 7-inch pan or 7 or 8-inch round pan, spreading quickly with spatula.
When fudge is firm, mark with sharp knife and cut into squares or remove from pan and break into irregular pieces.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Use 2 wafers for the bun.
Color icing red and yellow for ketchup and mustard.
Spread yellow on 1 wafer and red on the other.
Color coconut green and put on wafer for lettuce.
Add peppermint patty for hamburger.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
and
cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine soups, milk and enchilada sauce together.
Cover the bottom of a 13
x 9-inch
pan
with
small
amount of the soup mixture. Layer 1/3 of the tortilla pieces over the sauce.
Spread half of the
cooked chicken over the tortilla pieces.
Pour half of the sauce
mixture over
the
chicken.
Layer with 1/3 of the tortilla
pieces
and remaining chicken.
Pour remaining sauce over the chicken and layer
with
remaining
tortilla pieces. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake
at
for
about 1 hour.
Top with cheese during last 5 minutes of baking.
Serve with sour cream as a condiment.

title: pancakes
directions: In blender, combine bread crumbs, egg, baking powder, vanilla, sweetener and water.
Blend.
Drop by spoonfuls into a hot nonstick skillet.
Turn over when bubbles begin to burst.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Cream margarine with sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten egg. Add dissolved yeast to mixture.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight container.
Keep in refrigerator until needed (keeps 10-12 days).

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Cook rice and put in casserole (directions on rice).
Brown meat and onion; add pepper, spices and soup with milk.
Add mushrooms.
Add to rice and stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and tomato soup
directions: Boil noodles to directions on package; drain.
Add tomato juice.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine juice with next 5 ingredients.
Arrange chicken in baking pan skin side up.
Broil until browned.
Stir sauce; pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange lemon and pineapple slices around chicken. Spoon sauce from baking pan over all.
Continue baking 5 minutes. Garnish with fresh rosemary or parsley, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: sausage alfresco
directions: Cook fettuccini and keep warm.
Saute garlic and onion in large skillet with butter until tender.
Add vegetables and cook until done (5 minutes).
Set aside.
Brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Combine sausage, vegetables and cream.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Stir in parsley, cheese, salt and pepper.
Serve over fettuccine.
Sprinkle with extra cheese if desired.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart glass measuring cup. Microwave 5 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until tacky or about 2 minutes. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients except garnish until well blended.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: frosted pineapple
directions: Place chilled pineapple in 6 dessert dishes.
Sprinkle on 3/4 cup coconut.
Top with sherbet and scatter on remaining coconut. Garnish with blueberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and egg. Shape into individual meatballs. Mix tomato soup and water in pan. Add meatballs to soup mixture. Cook for 50 to 60 minutes on stove top. Stir occasionally.

title: "bread and circus" rice
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Cool.
In large bowl, place cooled rice.
Pour teriyaki over rice.
Toss lightly.
Add cashews, red peppers, raisins, scallions, apricots, celery and parsley; toss lightly.
In a small saucepan, heat oil.
Add dry mustard, curry, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Whisk until blended.
Cool. Whisk again and pour over ingredients in bowl.
Toss lightly; cool and enjoy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon bits.
Mix other ingredients together; pour over other mixture.
Mix well; chill before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until tender.
Add dry jello and sugar. When dissolved add crushed pineapple and chill until firm.

title: caramel peanut corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Beat down and pour over popped popcorn and peanuts in large mixing bowl.
Stir so all popcorn and nuts are covered.
Spread on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour in a 200° oven.
Cool and store in plastic bags.

title: quilters tea
directions: Mix above ingredients together. Store in air tight jar.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix
together
flour
and
sugar.
Add	slightly beaten eggs. Melt margarine.
Add to milk, then add to flour and egg mixture. Stir
in
coconut
and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields 2 pies.

title: hot crab souffle
directions: Cook celery slowly 10 minutes in a little water; drain.
Dice half the bread in 11-inch square baking dish.
Mix crab meat, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper and celery together.
Spread over bread.
Place remaining diced bread over crab mixture.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle with small amount of cheese and paprika.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: broccoli and ham soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender; not brown. Stir in flour, bouillon granules, mustard, thyme and pepper. Add milk and water all at once. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Stir in broccoli and ham. Return to boiling. Simmer 4 to 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: italian appetizer
directions: Slice and seed peppers.
Brush with olive oil.
Boil until peppers are slightly blistered.
Cool and chill in refrigerator, approximately 20 minutes or until slightly chilled.
Place peppers on serving platter.
Sprinkle generously with olive oil, chopped black olives, cheese and Italian seasonings.
Serve chilled as a cold salad or appetizer for an Italian dinner.

title: hawaiian delight pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and add the lemon juice. Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and chill at least 2 hours.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: First brown your hamburg, then put in a 8 x 10-inch pan, 2nd your rice (not cooked), 3rd 1 row green pepper, 4th sliced onion, then add your stewed tomatoes, then add slices of potatoes on top. Add salt and pepper.
