Before baking, add strips of bacon on top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon icebox pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together lemon juice, milk and Cool Whip.
Use wire whip, stir until smooth.
Pour mixture into crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add green pepper and mushrooms.
Mix in pizza sauce, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butter pecan crunch(elegant but easy)
directions: In bowl, combine crumbs and butter.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, ungreased.
Chill.
In a mixing bowl, beat pudding mixes and milk until well blended.
Fold in ice cream and Cool Whip.
Spoon over crust.
Sprinkle candy bars over.
Freeze.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: smitty's creamy clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Blend in flour.
Let bubble for a minute.
Stir in milk, mixing until heated through and slightly thickened.
Add clams, potatoes and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: lasagne
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown beef and onion.
Drain off as much fat as possible.
Add next 8 ingredients, ending with oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes.
Cook noodles in large amount boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place about 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Place half the noodles layered in baking dish; spread with half the cottage cheese filling.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.
Filling with set slightly.
Makes 12 servings.
Can be assembled early; refrigerate.
Allow 15 minutes longer in the oven.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: lean chicken gravy or lean beef gravy
directions: In a small saucepan, combine bouillon cubes, water and onion. Simmer gently 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally to dissolve bouillon cubes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine the pineapple, bananas, grapes, oranges and apples in a large bowl and set aside. In a saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add the orange juice and reserved pineapple juice.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Pour over fruit; mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix 3/4 of the tomatoes well at high speed in the mixer. Rejuvenate the dried onions in 1/4 cup water (hot).
Place the remaining 1/4 of the tomatoes in the mixer, together with all ingredients, except the flour and oil.
Beat this mixture well; put it in a pan with the rest of the tomatoes.
Cook this mixture for 5 minutes, checking to see if there is enough salt and pepper from time to time.
Add as necessary.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Melt the fat in the frying pan; add the onion and saute until tender.
Add the low sodium bread crumbs and seasonings and mix well.
Add the stock.
This is a light, loose stuffing.
It can be varied by leaving out the onion or the sage, by adding a little garlic or by adding unsalted nuts or raisins.

title: miss willie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend the first five ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Blend both mixtures together well.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool on a kitchen towel.

title: tropical salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: pocket stew
directions: Make 4 beef patties.
Peel carrots, potatoes and onions.
Add salt to beef mixture.
Slice onions and potatoes and cut carrots 2 to 3-inches in length.
Place each beef patty on aluminum foil, approximately 12 to 15-inches long.
Put several slices of potatoes and onions on patty; also the carrots.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat.
Crumble and drain off fat. Spread bread with oleo.
Cut into cubes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.

title: low-fat cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
May add water, if necessary. Pour into your favorite mold and bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix half and half with hash browns.
Melt butter and cheeses together.
Mix with hash brown mixture.
Cook on High in microwave for 15 minutes.
Stir well and cook for an additional 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6 people.
Recipe can be easily doubled.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into little balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered southwestern spread
directions: Combine Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, green chiles, mayonnaise and garlic; stir well.
Spread cheese mixture in 9-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Let cool about 3 minutes.

title: aunt's barbequed meat
directions: Brown meat in shortening until tender, then add all other ingredients and let simmer over low heat for 30 min.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix Knox
gelatine
with
the
Jell-O (dry), then add 2 cups hot
water.
Stir
until
dissolved, then add 2 cups cold water; stir.
Add the orange sherbet;
blend thoroughly.
In a separate bowl,
whip
container
heavy cream until thickened. Add to Jell-O
mixture; blend on low speed with mixer.
Drain the mandarin oranges; add to the Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate in bowl until almost thickened.
Stir and pour into Bundt pan.

title: sopaipillas (hot puffed bread)(about 3 dozen)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into bowl. Add milk and shortening to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Make a lengthwise slit in center of each strip. Fry in deep hot fat, 375°, about 2 minutes total time, tearing once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with syrup, honey or preserves.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and pie filling in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Slice margarine all over cake mix.
Cover with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab spread
directions: Press crabmeat between paper towel to absorb excess moisture. Combine crabmeat and green onions in a large bowl; set aside. Combine cream cheese and next 6 ingredients; add to crabmeat mixture, tossing to coat.
Cover crabmeat mixture.
Chill 8 hours.

title: marinated coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool; split into 4 layers.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Put filling generously between layers.
Mix reserved cup with Cool Whip and frost.
Keep refrigerated.
Make at least 24 hours before serving and up to 3 days early.
Keeps excellent; freezes excellent.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Get a medium bowl and put in sugar, cocoa, water, vinegar, salad oil and vanilla.
Mix.
Add your flour, salt and baking soda.
Make sure you have no lumps.
You put the mix in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan and bake for 30 minutes. Let cake cool and frost, or not, and eat.

title: crab florentine
directions: Spread spinach in bottom of 2 (9 x 13-inch) casseroles. Arrange crab on top of spinach.
Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Blend in wine and scallions.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Add salt, pepper and Old Bay seasoning to taste.
Add enough paprika to make sauce a rosy color.
Pour over crab.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Allow frozen casseroles 1 1/2 hours at 350° to cook through.
Yield:
2 (6 serving) casseroles.

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in 1 cup sugar.
Do not use the mixer after adding sugar.
Stir in the remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with 1 cup pecans.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Dump onto cloth with confectioners sugar.
While hot, roll up with cloth and cool completely.
Unroll and spread with filling. Reroll.
Chill or keep in freezer.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Brown onion, pepper and sausage.
Hollow out bread.
Crumble up bread crumbs into mixture and put in loaf.
Add slices of cheese on top.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves hot.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ice.
Add ice and serve at once.

title: alabama apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples into a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar; cover and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Put 2 beaten eggs into measuring cup.
Allow foam to recede.
Fill to one cup mark with cooking oil.
Pour over apples.
Stir well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy peas
directions: Mix and cook real slow, so it won't scorch, until cheese has blended well.

title: speedy fruit pie
directions: *Suggested Fruits:
Peaches, blueberries, blackberries and raspberries.

title: spicy rib stew
directions: In skillet, brown sausage, onion and garlic; transfer to 1 1/2-quart roasting/baking dish.
Stir in tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, chili, bouillon and oregano; set aside.
Cut ribs into 2-rib portions; brown in skillet.
Add ribs to stew, spooning juices over.
For make-ahead, seal and chill in refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, Karo and salt. Stir constantly until starts to boil.
Stop stirring.
Cook another 5 minutes. Remove from burner.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over popcorn, stir.
Place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Break up.

title: bonnie's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook bacon in nonstick skillet.
Drain fat.
Crumble and set aside.
Heat tortillas in 1 teaspoon of oil about 30 seconds or until soft.
Beat eggs and pepper in bowl.
Cook eggs in 1 teaspoon of oil.
Sprinkle cheese down center of tortilla.
Top with eggs and bacon.
Serve with salsa or catsup.

title: buttermilk-pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
(Sugar should be added gradually.)
Blend in vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Gradually add buttermilk.
Sprinkle pecans in pie shell.
Pour filling over pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve at room temperature.

title: mystery chef soup
directions: Place peas in large saucepan without lid and add 3 pints of cold water.
Bring to boiling point.
Allow to simmer until water cooks down and the peas are cooked to a soft wet paste.
Be careful not to let peas burn.
(Use heavy pan.)
Add the 2 cans of soup; stir and allow to simmer for a few minutes.
Season to taste.
If soup is too thick, add a little water.

title: apple nut torte
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 6 x 9-inch pan or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Then add flour and nuts.
Dough will be soft.
Divide in half and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread jam on top of dough.
Then spread remaining dough on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt all ingredients in a double boiler.
Use as a dip for apple slices.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion and mince garlic. Brown garlic, onion and beef. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly three hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in 1 tablespoon butter 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the soup, sour cream, pimentos and carrots.
Grease sides and bottom of casserole dish. Add the dressing and add mixture of squash, onion, soup, sour cream, pimento and carrots.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle a little dry dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter both sides of 2 slices of bread and cube in 1/2-inch cubes.
Cut remaining bread in 1-inch cubes.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place half of 1-inch cubes on bottom.
Combine meat, veggies, mayo and salt.
Spoon over bread cubes in pan, spread other half of 1-inch cubes over chicken mixture.
Mix milk and eggs and pour over all.
Cover and let chill overnight.

title: cabbage souffle casserole
directions: Cook
cabbage
in
boiling
salted
water until tender. Drain and
set
aside.
Spread
bread with margarine; place in large mixing
bowl.
Combine
eggs
and milk.
Pour over bread and allow to stand 5 minutes.
Add cabbage, 1 1/2 cups cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into greased 2 quart casserole.
Bake in 250°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with remaining
1 cup cheese; bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, 1/2 cup water and 3/4 cup margarine to 120° to 130°.
Add dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup flour and 2 eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter. Cover tightly and refrigerate 2 hours or up until 2 days.
Turn on floured board, roll into four 12-inch circles; brush with melted margarine; sprinkle with lemon peel.
Cut each circle into 8 wedges.
Roll up loosely; curve to form a crescent.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Combine egg yolk and water; brush rolls and sprinkle with sugar.
Let rise until doubled (45 minutes).
Bake at 400°, for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 32 rolls.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender (cut in bite size pieces).
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Put chicken in a casserole and pour sour cream and soup mixture with chicken.
Put cracker crumbs over the chicken, then pour melted oleo over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients; let rise for 2 hours.
Knead down into rolls in a greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Once out of oven, put butter on top of rolls.
Makes 16 to 20 rolls.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Use as dessert or fruit salad.

title: surprise spread
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread over a 12 inch pizza pan.
Scatter shrimp over the cheese mixture; add a layer of seafood sauce, cheese, green pepper, onions and tomato.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana macadamia nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs, baking soda, salt and orange peel.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating about 1 minute, well mixed.
Stir in coconut and nuts (batter will be thick).
Spread into 1 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 35 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool. Bake at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook rice according to package directions until partially done.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 1 hour longer, stirring several times.

title: fat-free blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix only until blended.
Spray large muffin pan with Pam.
Distribute mix in pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs
in large bowl. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine
dry
ingredients. Add to egg mixture; blend well.
Stir
in
nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves. You may add less cinnamon, if you like.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken stock.
While broccoli is cooking, prepare the White Sauce.
Combine and heat, stirring until blended and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Beat egg yolk with fork and blend in cream.
Stirring constantly, stir egg mixture slowly into broccoli mixture and heat.
Cover and keep warm until serving time.
Add butter just before serving.
(Two cups of fresh broccoli may be substituted for the frozen broccoli.)

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: one cup cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: kyle's special sandwich
directions: Toast bagel. Place cheese on lunch meat and microwave until cheese is melted. Spread peanut butter onto toasted bagel. Place meat and cheese on bagel. Pour teaspoon of honey on late for exquisite additional taste.

title: easy chicken and dumplin's
directions: Use no salt.
Boil chicken and debone.
Add to broth, the bouillon cubes.
Sprinkle the flour over the tortillas and cut into 1-inch or 2-inch pieces.
Drop in the boiling broth slowly. Cook 30 minutes.
Add the chicken, then add the milk.
Let set for 15 minutes and then serve.

title: jerry's easy fruit salad
directions: Mix peach pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, oranges, cherries and pecans.
Sprinkle pudding mix over the mixture.
Stir and chill.
Before serving, cut up bananas and add.
Quick, easy and good.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk and stir until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Then add oranges, pineapple and cookies (broken into small pieces).

title: heavenly fudge sauce
directions: Combine everything in medium saucepan. Heat over medium heat for about 15 minutes, until mixture boils. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Yields 3 cups. Serve with ice cream or fresh fruits.

title: orangey green beans with crispy onions
directions: In saucepan, bring water to the boil.
Add beans and cook until tender, about 7 to 9 minutes; drain.
Combine vinegar, garlic, zest, salt and pepper until salt dissolves.
Slowly whisk in oil until mixture thickens slightly.
In serving bowl, combine beans with vinaigrette until coated.
Set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in milk and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
This is good with apples, grapes or strawberries.

title: beer batter
directions: Stir eggs slightly to break yolks.
Add beer and salt (gently).
Add flour, leaving it lumpy.
Flour and season fish and then dip fish into batter.
Drop into hot fat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add juice, egg and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in gently.
Add any fruits, about 4 cups pineapple, strawberries, bananas, grapes, apples and nuts.

title: mercedes chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, oleo and shortening.
Make a well in the mixture.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add flour, Minute oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Mix beans and salsa, spread over large pie plate or quiche dish.
Spread guacamole over beans.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream, spread over guacamole layer.
Sprinkle with cheese, tomatoes, black olives, and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream all; chill, roll out and bake at 350°.

title: colcannon
directions: Choose casserole according to number of servings desired and adjust ingredients accordingly.

title: mustard sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine mustard, sugar and salt.
Add vinegar and egg blending well.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Store in refrigerator.

title: light and fluffy pancakes(makes 8)
directions: Melt butter.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat together melted butter, egg and milk.
Stir wet ingredients into dry until just combined.
It's all right if the batter is still
lumpy.
Heat pan on medium-high heat.
Brush pan with oil. Pour 1/4 cup into pan, making a few pancakes at a time.
Cook until bubbles burst.
Turn and cook until underside is golden. Repeat with remaining batter until all is used.

title: annabeth's favorite sausage foldovers
directions: Pack children in car.
Go through drive-thru window at Michna's Barbecue on Franklin.
Order 2 sausage foldovers on white bread with mustard (hold the sauce).
Throw food to kids.
Put change in pocket and drive to next stop.

title: venison sauerbraten
directions: Cover meat with vinegar, water, onions, bay leaves, cloves, salt, pepper and sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours. Remove from marinade and wipe dry.
Brown meat in hot fat.
Place meat on rack in heavy 4-quart skillet or Dutch oven.
Strain marinade and add 3 cups to pan.
Cover.
Simmer slowly 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy with crumbled gingersnaps.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monterey souffle
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, and peanut butter.
Cream until light.
Add salt and soda to flour.
Mix well with egg mixture.
Roll into little balls. Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Mash flat with a fork.
Bake at 300° for about 7 minutes.

title: krafty crescent lasagna
directions: On foil-lined baking sheet, lay out crescent rolls to form one large rectangle.
Pinch all perforations together.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper. Combine cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan.
Spread meat mix down center of crescent roll rectangle.
Top with cottage cheese mixture.
Spread Mozzarella slices to cover.

title: baking mix
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl in order given.
Cut margarine into flour mix until mixture resembles coarse grain.
Store in tightly covered jar (I refrigerate).
Keeps well.
A good substitute for Bisquick.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Mix
margarine, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Spread
over
both	insides
of
rolls.
Place in baking pan
placing one slice of ham and one slice of cheese on bottom half
of
roll.
Place top half on this and bake at 350° until cheese
begins
to	melt.
(Ham and cheese slices cut to size of roll.)

title: ciambelone italian coffee cake
directions: Mix all together as for cake.
Grease an angel food pan; pour batter in.
Sprinkle sugar over batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute peppers and onions in peanut oil.
Add shrimp and water chestnuts; cook 4 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients with rice and saute in peanut oil until well heated.

title: freeze-ahead chicken
directions: Buy boneless breast of chicken in larger amounts.
Rinse well and put the number of pieces of chicken needed for your family in plastic freezer bags.
Add one of the listed marinades.
Grill 5 minutes on each side or bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes or until juice runs clear.

title: pizza margherita
directions: Brush crust (dough) with oil.
Spoon topping over dough. Arrange cheese over pizza.

Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste, 2 to 3 basil leaves and remaining oil. Bake 20 minutes until cheese has melted and dough looks crisp and golden. Sprinkle with remaining basil leaves. Serve at once.

title: busy day dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients (except elbow macaroni) in a saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and simmer gently, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cook elbow macaroni, then add to the finished ingredients.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Let soak 8 hours.
Drain.
Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add beans, salt, pepper, chopped tomato, water and vinegar.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato paste.
Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Top each serving with tomato, green onions and yogurt.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, hamburger and noodles.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese has browned.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples thin; add sugar and cinnamon.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well. Add all other ingredients and stir together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In large mixing bowl cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs one
at
a	time,
mixing well after each one.
Stir flour and baking
powder
together; add milk and flour alternately beginning and ending with milk.
Add extract.
Fold in peaches.
Pour in
a tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until	cake
tester is	inserted
in
center and comes out clean.
Cool
completely in	pan.
Remove and place on plate. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pecan waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add pecans.
Beat egg yolks until light combine with milk and melted shortening and add to dry ingredients, mixing just until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then onion.
Add buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Drop into hot cooking oil by teaspoonfuls.

title: hard time cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and soda 3 times. Work shortening in flour mixture as for a biscuit. Add sugar, then the buttermilk and vanilla. Roll and cut. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased bowl and set bowl in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: olive and cheese dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, ham, milk, onion, Worcestershire and dry mustard with electric mixer until fluffy. Fold in the chopped olives.
Chill until ready to serve.
If necessary, thin with additional milk.
Garnish with sliced olives. Serve with potato chips or vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: batter dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together for a vegetable dip for deep frying.
Very good for zucchini.

title: golden egg bread
directions: Bread Machine:
Combine ingredients in the order given and bake on white bread setting.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in ice water and let set for 1 hour.
Drain and add the pimento.
Salt to taste, then set aside.

title: mousse au chocolat(chocolate mousse)
directions: Break chocolate into small
pieces
and put on a plate. Cover with another plate.
Put
the
plates over a saucepan of simmering water and leave
for
10 minutes until the chocolate has melted. Beat the egg yolks in a mixer until they are very thick.
Fold in the
butter,
orange liqueur and melted chocolate.	Beat the egg whites
until they form soft peaks.
Fold chocolate mixture into the
egg
whites
with
a wooden spoon. Divide mixture among 6 small
dishes.
Chill
hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Cut bacon, peppers and onions into chunks.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix and serve over chicken, rice, beef or pork.

title: molded neptune salad
directions: Stir tomato soup and cream cheese in double boiler.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup mixture until fully dissolved. Cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in square Pyrex dish until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: foil dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut carrots, celery, onion and potatoes into bite size pieces.
Wash chicken under cold water and pat dry. Place 1 piece of chicken and 1/4 of the vegetables on each of 4 pieces of aluminum foil.
Add a pat of butter to each and season with salt and pepper.
Bring foil up over chicken and fold edges tightly.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken and potatoes are tender.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix well. Press in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: busy day stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat and serve with toast or crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 4 or 5 cups salted water until done.
Cool and cut into bite sized pieces.
Cook vegetables in skillet with sausage until limp.
At this point, mix all ingredients together well and pour into an oblong pan.
Whip the can of mushroom soup and spoon over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside.
In the same kettle, saute onions in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved broth until soup is of desired consistency.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo in squash. Add soup in another bowl. Add and mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Add bread crumbs and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken first into flour, coating well, then into eggs, which have been beaten slightly and diluted with the milk, then into crumbs.
Coat well and shake off excess.
Preheat frypan to 360°.
Add fat.
Place cover in spatter shield position.
Brown chicken without overcrowding, turning all sides to brown.
Remove browned pieces to a pie pan.
Scrape out breading particles and add more shortening before browning next batch.
When all pieces are browned, place chicken in frypan; sprinkle evenly with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add water and scatter onions over chicken.
Cover; open vent.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until chicken is very tender.
Remove chicken to heated platter.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased bread pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° until tests done with toothpick.

title: best oven hash
directions: Lightly mix first 8 ingredients.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs or chips with melted margarine. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan. Beat eggs and sugar. Add carrots, pineapple and oil. Blend. Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well. Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check for doneness before 1 hour.

title: fruit salad(with sour cream)
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine and put in crock or slow cooker for about 2 hours or longer.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon; mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set. Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Spread sour cream on top.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in saucepan and heat until warm.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into a glass baking dish, spreading evenly.
Toast at 400° for about 20 minutes; stir frequently.
Turn out on paper towels and sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: posole pronto
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions in oil, then brown the pork. Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, until pork is tender, about 4 hours. Serve in bowls as soup with crackers or warmed flour tortillas.

title: fruity punch
directions: *(This is a non-alcoholic concentrate found in the frozen juice section.)

title: beef sherry
directions: Bake at 325° for 3 hours or in crock-pot on low all day.
Serve with egg noodles or rice.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to heated mixture. Cook to thicken. Place in jars and store in refrigerator.

title: sara's sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix soda with buttermilk until it foams.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat in flour.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry maple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the apples, apple juice, cranberries, cinnamon and salt in an ungreased 8-inch square pan.

title: crisp waffles
directions: Mix all together until smooth. Let set 5 minutes before cooking.
Good for freezing.
Just pop in toaster.

title: celery casserole
directions: Saute celery in margarine until tender.
Add nuts and green pepper; blend in flour.
Stir in warm milk and cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: marshmallow cups
directions: Line 18 mini muffin cups with double thickness paper cups. Set aside.
Melt chips with shortening in heavy, small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour into shortening in a large bowl.
Beat egg in a measuring cup.
Add vinegar to egg.
Add enough water to egg mixture to make 1 cup.
Mix with flour.
Roll out for pie crust. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: fresh squeezed orange juice
directions: Cut hole in top of orange or cut orange in half.
Squeeze into glass.
Take seeds out.
Makes 1 glass.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let half jell.
Beat whipping cream or dessert mix.
When Jell-O is half jelled, beat for 2 minutes, then pour in whipped cream and beat until frothy.
Mix all other ingredients and put in freezer for a few minutes so that all ingredients don't go to the bottom.

title: oven baked apple pancakes with sausage
directions: Stir melted butter into blended milk and egg.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients and apple to liquid mixture; beat just enough to mix ingredients.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish (or large cast-iron skillet is good), which has been lightly rubbed or sprayed with oil.
Arrange sausage on top of the batter.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: greek bread
directions: Set bread out and let rise.
Cook sausage well.
Cook spinach following directions on package and drain.
Mix sausage, spinach and cheese.
Add onion salt to taste.
Roll out loaves of frozen bread (loaves will be hard to roll out).
Sprinkle one half of sausage mixture on each loaf leaving room around edges.
Roll up into logs and put into lightly greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 15 minutes before slicing.

title: luke's favorite pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs until light.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: 5 o'clock buns
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients and add the flour.
Work the dough until dough does not stick to your hands.
Put in bowl and cover.
Knead down every hour.
Shape into buns or rolls (not too large).
Cover overnight.
In the morning bake at 350° until brown.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil the oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Mix with dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs (well beaten).
Mix well. Makes one 9 x 13-inch pan and one 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in one bowl.
Melt margarine in another bowl.
Separate biscuits in half across layers.
Dip into margarine, then into cinnamon mixture, turning over.
Put back together and twist.
Put into cupcake pans and bake according to package directions.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pack tightly in pan and cover with foil. Chill several hours before serving.

title: turkey hash
directions: Heat oil and margarine.
Saute vegetables until soft.
Add turkey, potatoes and seasonings.
Stir to combine and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch or smaller baking dish.
Bake at 400° until top is crusty and brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: granola
directions: Heat honey, oil and vanilla.
Mix first 9 ingredients and pour honey mixture over; stir.
Bake in low oven (250° to 275°) for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Add fruit.
Store in covered container and refrigerate.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates into small pieces in medium size bowl; pour boiling water over and stir in sugar and margarine.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in beaten egg and walnuts.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Stir gradually into date mixture just until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan, 9 x 15 x 13-inch.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blue bonnet cafe apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine the sugar, flour and spices in a large bowl. Add the apple slices and toss until they are well coated. Fill the crust with the apple slices and dot them with the butter.

Ease the top crust over the filled bottom crust; trim and seal the edges. Cut slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape. Bake 1 hour or until crust is golden and the apples test done. Turn off the oven and remove the pie. Gently pour the cream through the slits in the crust. Return the pie to the oven and leave it there about 20 minutes.

title: corn and broccoli medley(easy!  excellent!)
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add corn and broccoli; mix well.
Add crackers; mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basic yellow cake
directions: Cream butter until it is light and fluffy.
Add sugar, a little at a time, mixing after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder three times.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, adding a bit of flour last.
Beat egg whites and add to batter, using a folding method.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan, three 9-inch pans, sheet cake pan or make muffins.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when pressed with fore finger. Frost with your favorite frosting or enjoy plain.

title: slow cooker beef stew
directions: Place the carrots, potatoes, mushrooms, onion and celery in the slow cooker. Place the stew meat over the vegetables. In a medium bowl, combine the soup mix with the can of soup. Add the water and mix together well. Pour this in the slow cooker over the meat and vegetables. Add water as needed so that the liquid comes just to the bottom of the meat. Cook on low setting overnight, adding more water as necessary in the morning. Allow to cook all day.

title: mexican rice
directions: Mix well. Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Place each chicken breast on a square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Combine soup and soup mix; spread on half each chicken breast.
Wrap foil securely.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunked cantaloupe, honeydew melon, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: football lover's stew
directions: In large kettle or heavy saucepot, saute bacon until golden brown; remove and set aside. Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge meat in flour mixture.
Brown meat over high heat, a few pieces at a time, in bacon fat.
Remove and reserve.
Add olive oil; heat.
Saute onion and garlic until golden.
Add orange juice, wine, tomato puree, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, nutmeg and bay leaves.
Return bacon and meat to kettle.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon ring
directions: Blend everything except biscuits, then stir in biscuits to coat.
Bake in Bundt pan 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Let cool 2 to 3 minutes, then cover with a large plate. Hold it over the sink and turn it away from you as you invert the pan.

title: yeast bread
directions: Put yeast to set in warm water and melt shortening and scald milk.
Let both cool to lukewarm.
Then put into mixing bowl the milk, shortening, salt, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add yeast and egg; mix well.
Then add rest of flour.
Mix well.
Turn on floured board and knead about 20 times.
Make out into rolls; let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Make 3 slits lengthwise in each eggplant.
In each slit, put half slice of anchovy, a sliver of cheese, slice of garlic and small sprig of parsley.
After all eggplants are stuffed, heat oil in a large saucepan and brown eggplants on all sides.
Place the eggplants in saucepan after all are browned and pour tomato sauce over eggplants.
Sprinkle some black pepper, some basil and salt in sauce and let simmer until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
The tomato sauce can be poured over cooked rice or noodles.
If you like to dunk, Italian bread dunked in the sauce is just fine!

title: unrolled cabbage
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper, uncooked rice and 1/4 cup onions together; then add tomatoes, brown sugar, vinegar, 2 tablespoons chopped onions and tomato paste.
Layer cabbage, meat and sauce two times.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered, then uncover and bake for 3 hours at 250°.
